{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'OAG3fQURGrwKmxfIl-1g-A', 'review_id': 'wxmQ_H5lxcwh4m7xD4tT2w', 'text': 'awesome meal - we hit the first day of Restaurant week by chance and had the opportunity to have the Prix Fix menu - awesome scallops, chicken, and yeah, the Chop Salad is as unbelievable as your server says it is.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-05-22', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 4, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': 'OcC0jD5x6dCV2n7oZ8B3hQ', 'review_id': 'AiPv0O_HWH_hCGm-uHK9Xg', 'text': "We were really excited about trying this place on our trip to Scottsdale and were a little dismayed to learn it was Restaurant Week when we arrived (in Denver, Restaurant Week can sometimes mean a decline in food quality and service...). We decided to order off the regular menu and everything we got was so delicious. The burrata was great and was served on top of an eggplant puree--I hadn't burrata served like that before, but really enjoyed it. I ordered the rockfish which was great; however, the curried millet with okra that it was served with stole the show for me. I seriously could eat that every day and might have to try to recreate it at home. My husband ordered a fish that was the special for the evening. I can't remember what it was, nor did I try it (isn't this review incredibly helpful??) but he did say he loved it and ate every bit, so that can't be a bad thing ;) Peach and berry pie for dessert was great, although it was heavy on the berries and light on the peach. But who can really complain about that? The service was great; our server was attentive and the food was timed nicely. Overall a great experience!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2013-05-25', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'f8r71PyNRbajpCsd3AB2pg', 'review_id': '5a3BhrRSYtu9Lj6ccPPNkA', 'text': 'Great! Busy in a good way. A lot of pretty people, but the drinks and chow prove this place is legit. First, the barkeeps aren\'t hick town slingers. Enjoyed a Sazarac so smooth I should have bought it breakfast. Piggy & Waffle app made me wonder why the folks in the South stick with chicken... Damn! Roasted chicken and Brussels sprouts was not messing around, though the mantra "never eat anyone\'s meatloaf but your mothers\'s" was reinforced with a nice attempt, but not a home run. Dessert, drinks, wine, and service were all fantastic. Big recommend.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-05-26', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '0rLWHgBu8xwXqPvs2MaQ3A', 'review_id': 'FKBxkfaYtMNvBQi3vU0mAQ', 'text': 'Great food. Unique mixed drinks. Their chopped salad may be the best salad ever eaten.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-05-27', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'Z-rdg43tHjjp8czweAttdA', 'review_id': 'Bx-jMkKpsvwT4HZ9w5QBKw', 'text': "Great food.  We ordered several dishes and each had it's own unique flavor.  Both the meatloaf and the scallops were excellent.  They also make a good Moscow Mule.  Service was great as well.  If you're in town, stop by.  You can't go wrong.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-05-27', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'jOFAuhmxts3TIi-QkIiX9A', 'review_id': 'UAZAjH2OGRlrHino2PosFA', 'text': "The dinner and drinks at Citizen Public House were out of this world! My dining companions drank the Im-port, made with house made tobacco & leather infused bitters-- seriously???  They raved about it!  My club soda was also poured to perfection.  I think they should make it a feature on the menu.\nAs an appetizer we had the pork belly pastrami, which is served with rye spaetzle, and brussels sprout sauerkraut.  It was delicious.  I had a little of the chopped salad.  It was delicious as always.  It is originally from the Cowboy Ciao menu, and has been a favorite of mine (and everyone else) for years.   The soup of the day was the tomato bisque, and it was very good too.  The scallops were perfectly cooked.  I sampled some of the beef short ribs.  They were some of the best ribs I have eaten in years.  I would definitely order them the next time I dine at CPH.  For dessert we shared the PB & B bread pudding.  It was the only thing that I didn't love.   It was a little dry.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-05-27', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'jZWP12U0SgpjCuhL3lGGvw', 'review_id': 'TMKYelJ9qwAUbN1X7_gHUg', 'text': 'Really not sure what all the hype is about.  Ate here about 3 weeks ago and it was nothing but forgetful - no really had to look at menu to figure out what we ate...  \nHe -  the scallops, they were good enough\nShe (me) - the short ribs.  Not very tender and just OK.  I can make them better.  \nBurrata was our starter -  Good but again nothing that left any real impression.\n\nNot the type of place that left me thinking "Gosh I cant wait to return".  Probably wont.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 2, 'date': '2013-05-28', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'YrbcT9CB_kW3RQutizG4Uw', 'review_id': 'w6OM8WQrKWWPNceI2X_CQA', 'text': 'Came here for restaurant week and I was impressed!  The chopped salad was interesting, looked beautiful, and very tasty.  The scallops were cooked well and the grits were creamy and delicious.  I scraped up every last bit of grit off the plate.  The PB&B banana pudding was good though I did wish I had chosen the mint chocolate cake instead.  For restaurant week I usually slightly lower my expectations knowing that the kitchen is preparing large quantities of the same dishes for less $$, but Citizen Public House did not disappoint!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-05-28', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'jEQHhBlzhW1PdbBXMC-2SQ', 'review_id': 'UoDI2u-4Ed7qT2HRwqWAVQ', 'text': "Great atmosphere, great service, great drinks, good food. Yes, the chopped salad is amazing. Lamb burger is solid, but the other entrees at my table (meatloaf and scallops) weren't anything to write home about. Would definitely come back to sit at the bar for a cocktail or two and try some more of the apps.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2013-05-30', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '5cxCKTziUlcLAeKFOhpFjQ', 'review_id': 'XhwG4kStGSqw36ovICq7aw', 'text': 'Meh. Mediocre at best. Service was horrible. It took 20 min to get drinks and then we were asked if we would like to order appetizers.  I may have enjoyed the food but I was turned off by the service.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 2, 'date': '2013-05-31', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 5, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': 'Eu5MjwCQiWvBFA9uzGlAoA', 'review_id': '3eVXetbKM-ay5EFxpmAQrg', 'text': "Coulda been a 4 star rating but the excellent customer service makes CPH a 5-star in my book.\n\nOnce we were seated our waiter Matt greeted us and made us feel welcome. His easy going demeanor and sense of humor make CPH look good and he could teach lessons to some waiters I've known. \n\nCPH makes their own barrel cocktails aged and flavored right in the restaurant. We were undecided on which to try ($5 each during happy hour, usually $12) so Matt brought us a sample of each. All were interesting and unique and we ended up ordering the Negroni, the Pyrat Eye the Craftsman along with an appetizer of rosemary nuts and green olives. Great way to start a meal!\n\nOur dishes included the Seared Scallops (heaven on a plate), the Fried Bologna Sandwich (delicious mortadella and pistachios) and the Grilled Lamb Loin (perfectly cooked and seasoned). Dinner cocktails included the Citi-Zen, a pear vodka concoction topped with rock candy; the Hot Pink Paloma, a paloma with a light, zesty pepper taste; and a Persian, made with wild tea vodka and cucumber...super refreshing!\n\nFinished dinner with Irish Coffee and a take home bag of bacon brittle. \n\nWhile dining we noticed two employees putting two tables together for a party and actually taking the time to adjust the lighting so as to make sure none of the ceiling lights would be in any of the incoming diners eyes. Impressive and caring enough to make sure all the details were right.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-06-02', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'VGXYc_r-jDjyhqhlWNs91Q', 'review_id': '1Kgu7cf3D1AjSKF6zvKgzg', 'text': "I thought this place was good! Great atmosphere, but not sure what the hype is about. Maybe I ordered the wrong plate (roasted chicken for restaurant week). The famous chopped salad was really good. I will give them that. \n\nI would come back to CPH, but I won't race back.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2013-06-04', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '2hXL2ExBsgjJNpm6BJy0lg', 'review_id': 'GEZyQG-81bz_aIx0iWR2Ig', 'text': "Citizen Public House is awesome! I've been here twice now, and am wondering why I don't go more often. The food, drinks, & service is impeccable, and the ambiance is great. \nHere's the breakdown of what I've tried so far:\n- bacon popcorn: you really can't go wrong with popcorn cooked in bacon fat and bacon pieces\n- chopped salad: this salad has it's own facebook page for a reason, I had a sample of this at an event and that is what brought me here to begin with. https://www.facebook.com/TheOriginalChoppedSalad?fref=ts\n- watermelon & halloumi salad: marinated sweet watermelon chunks with tangy halloumi, so good\n- pork belly pastrami: simple but so flavorful\n- burrata: creamy goodness, fresh ingredients, you can't not like this\n- scallops: generously sized scallops with bacon, cooked perfectly\n- rockfish: served with a mild curry sauce, also cooked perfectly, also a generous portion\nI would highly recommend Citizen as it's one of my favorite Phoenix restaurants!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-06-08', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'HurztSvU6a1PoS4snvqlHw', 'review_id': 'sIpshLcgAgMfNHvVAcVzEw', 'text': "This is a great place for sophisticated, but reasonably priced food!  We've been here a couple times and everything that we've ordered was delicious.  You can't go wrong with the scallops and the duck.  We will definitely go back!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2013-06-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'fMyClIBl_2KW0B5VuRaosg', 'review_id': 'hsucbRa5elJdttyrvilxIw', 'text': "I'm not sure what the hype is about.\nThe good:  Great space (Atmosphere, crowd, ambiance, decor), great service.\nThe okay:  Food was mediocre.  Seriously, everyone at the table was not impressed with their meal.  Bad night?   I appreciate chef's exploring, but do that on your own time.  The chef was trying to be creative, I get that.  But the flavors, textures and aromas - nothing harmonized. I literally had an upset stomach afterwards.\n\nAnywhos, if you're looking for a kitschy place to take a date and not worrying about an impressive meal, this is your place.  Or if you just want cocktails, this is the place.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 2, 'date': '2013-06-12', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '30_2QnM27XvV7g2QtlCrXA', 'review_id': '1JQ7sYpxQRgASSJt4yHvBQ', 'text': "I enjoyed my visit to Citizen Public House last night  ....\n\nWe had a handful of yummy apps.  My favorites were the WaterMelon Argula Salad & Crab Cakes.   Not to be overlooked, was the adult beverage menu.  I was sold on the Persian Cucumber cocktail.   #Yum\n\nMy friend ordered the Bacon Brittle to-go, from the Desert Menu.   Do yourself a favor and skip that.   It's a slippery slope to lighting bacon-flavored candles in your home.\n\nCertainly going back.  Good Service & nice Atmosphere.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2013-06-13', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'JIhvnvszdtOjOI3arLTozA', 'review_id': 'Xa9utRGzsN4w_LUtRuFYzA', 'text': 'Everything was very good, especially the chopped salad, get the chopped salad! I had it weeks ago and I still think about it...The restaurant was beautiful and the service was nice.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-06-19', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Qv_tTd1kjURtauJg6-DptQ', 'review_id': 'L7PXV-jRlk2IHEUxzU4yKg', 'text': "This place rocks. The real deal.  Late night menu is a real treat.  Superb mixologists at the bar.  Mind blowing cocktails.  High quality food that's fresh and scrumptious.  I love going here prior to partying in Old Town Scottsdale.  Very sexy establishment.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-06-22', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'QsaF7ao-kMpvF_Out81DwA', 'review_id': 'LoV_-JJGEjo2VAdhtUMRPA', 'text': "Having read these reviews i expected more. So very compelled to review myself. \n\nService excellent, atmosphere classy and chill, menu, same as atmosphere. \n\nGastronomically this place is classy, definitely aspires for that modern blend of fresh farm ingredients and high fat natural  elements like butter, cream bacon and cheese. TOO much bacon on this menu for sure, jews and muslims must not apply. \n\nFood:\n\nPita and Hummus from Bar side of Menu: Oddly the best of the 7 things we had! I ate it up! the pita is too good, i think it's fresh baked, falls apart into s gooey bready goodness, the eggplant hummus amazing especially when combined with these little sour pickles that it's served with. YUM\n\nGaspacho- the tomato puree with slices of cucumber and radish was only ok, flavor profile definitely weak, resembled baby food to me and i LOVE good gaspacho, could have backed a little kick, even pepper would improve it, but the 2 shrimps that came inside it were cooked to painful perfection. Definitely executed well, the recipe itself is blah, won't have again. \n\nChopped salad- everyone raves about this salad, and it's good, but it's really not that good at all, it's own facebook page? ah sounds like a fad to me, the dry freezed corn in it is a let down, it's crunchy sure, but the seeds are enough crunch in there, but actual corn like grilled off the cob would have given this salad a gravitas it really needs, ground it, earthy it up, because it's  very light, it's got lox and seeds and etc so it's got various textures, but somehow nothing stands out so it's like a pleasant mush in your mouth, i think most of all it could be improved by a better dressing than the generic ranch it comes with, i might have had an entirely different impression of it if the dressing was lighter, sweeter, more acidic and again perhaps more peppery or spicy-sorry to say but this salad didn't stand out for me, and i live for salad\n\nWatermelon salad- very different, never had anything like it, worth having just to try, beautiful on the eyes, but really is more of  cheese and watermelon plate, playing on the old and wonderful combo of fruit & cheese, take a bite of your watermelon with a bite of the cheese and maybe a salad leaf, it's tasty. \n\nScallops- Good normal well assembled dish....TOO MUCH BACON, must the gorgeous delicacy of a well prepped scallop always be obstructed by bacon? Over wrought, I feel like this trend ought to be retired, i get the appeal of surfy turfy plates, but scallops themselves are enough, i don't need them floating in bacon fat(not literally, they are served beautifully) surrounded by chunks of piggy, it's not that clever bringing the demise of these very contrary creatures onto the same playing field, we get it, none of gods creatures are safe when humans crack open their cookbooks, the novelty has long worn off for me, decadence is better served by letting one or the other shine, and not having them struggle on a plate for attention like two adopted siblings. \n\nGrilled cheese sandwich - Sort of awesome if you are willing to take in about a weeks worth of fat and cholesterol, it's stuffed with mashed potatoes, you can taste the cream in them, truffle oil, caramelized onions and cheese, bread is soaked in butter cooked with egg, it's rich as hell, tastes really good, i could go with a little less rich and  little less butter, but i am not sure if the function of a good grilled cheese sandwich is not precisely to be rich, so i am torn. I think though i would have enjoyed it more if it wasn't such a heartattack cubed on a plate, came with a cute salad i enjoyed, and strange throw away veggies that looked better than they tasted.\n\nBread Pudding: We had to send it back, may be the worst i ever had, and that's rough but not an exaggeration. Hard dry old tasting coarse bread situation with icecream on top. Huge let down and not consistent with the quality of the food they served prior to it. i expect something of sublime quality even if not to my taste, but it was just a yucky afterthought. \n\nPros: other than the Bread Pudding food is quality, carefully assembled, thought out fresh and pretty. Everything is Cooked right. Service GREAT \n\nCons: Bread basket, stale and boring with surprisingly not good olive oil. no way to start a meal.\n No coffee drinks other than espresso and no milk variations other than whole. a non fat latte would have really made my night. \n\nHappy dining.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2013-06-24', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 4, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': '2h0A-NirfNl2p2SquFWYHQ', 'review_id': '-DPuejIGhpjl-TX0RzHgGA', 'text': 'I kept saying "I haven\'t been to Citizen Public House" and everyone was like "What?".  I can say I have been and I have enjoyed every visit.  You have the best Mixologists I have come across!  Those crazy concoctions are AMAZING!  My favorites include the Old Fashioned and Manhattan.  I have been told by a close source, Mandi B., that the Handcrafted Sangria is delicious.  The Hummus & Tzatziki is the best I have ever tasted.  Everything tastes so fresh and good.  The Bacon Fat Heirloom Popcorn is a fantastic starter.  I have only been here for drinks and light bites.  The Chopped Salad was the best salad I\'ve ever tasted and I hate salads.  I need to come back and try some items off the dinner menu to have the whole CPH experience!  \n\nP.S.  CPH has social hour everyday 3-6pm!!!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2013-06-27', 'type': 'review'}
