{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 2, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 't3lFE9o_MvISntK3lXE36A', 'review_id': 'NzLRwVRB3oYypVV7WVelug', 'text': 'Went here to grab some dinner for one while my husband was at a conference. Greeted with really good service at the bar and they were nice enough to charge my phone while i ate, so that i could find my way back to our hotel...\n\nI had a glass of Chardonnay and the Short Ribs. The short ribs were well cooked and seasoned and once you dip it in the bbq sauce it was just perfect. The portion size is small considering the price ($30). Thats even pricey by NYC standards.\n\nOverall really good. The bartenders look like they know what theyre doing. They were shaking the drinks properly. I love when there are some ice chips in my drink!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-01-13', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'BGosDKjgskC6VzpWX0JfHg', 'review_id': 'x1WFVVyniES2a0eFD5kZOw', 'text': "Yes, the Chopped Salad is as good as everyone says it is. And yes, you can order almost anything off the menu and be pleased with it (though the meatloaf is average). \nWhat really shines through is the service here. Seriously, it's definitely in my top 5 best restaurants for outstanding service.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-01-16', 'type': 'review'}
