{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '7W_gDiXzjAQw5Hfmo31RSw', 'review_id': 'jYO_ZPEwBBBxi1ut_Sv5tw', 'text': "Love, love, love all the beer on tab selections! The food was absolutely amazing too. Definitely will be returning and can't wait to try all those delicious beers! \n\nNothing to complain about here, did I mention the great service?", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-01-20', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '6xV63p25A6M5dDCq8pVf9g', 'review_id': 'rhGWXs49CnH2ZXSv4RtcgQ', 'text': 'I first heard about this restaurant when our son came home for a visit and showed me a picture of \'the best chopped salad I\'ve ever had, Mom." So when we came out to visit him, we headed there. Our waiter was simply amazing - attentive but not hovering, very very helpful in choosing a wine (and letting me take a pic of the bottle so I could remember it!). He remembered our son from his previous visits. \nThe chopped salad lived up to the raves. The smoked salmon and dehydrated corn made all the difference in the taste and texture. It was simply amazing! My mushroom tartlet was earthy and tasty with some great light crust. \nA must visit for Scottsdale!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-01-26', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'CNecF-hWfSqo_KBzPi3oSA', 'review_id': '7RnaEkTuK_HVt9kbRjVjAA', 'text': 'Headed here after picking my husband up from the airport on a Wednesday night - a little nicer than I was going for, as we were pretty casual, but very nice atmosphere.  The scallops were to die for, and I had a really tasty seasonal mule.  Would definitely dine here again.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-01-27', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'n3ah5obJtggyKIA8oAaAuA', 'review_id': 'r34MAsWGaHot12snFSDB-g', 'text': 'Citizen Public House is one of my most favorite restaurants in Scottsdale and definitely on one of my tops just overall.  I had been taken here by some colleagues who are more local to the area and I\'ve gone back a good 3 times because I just like it that much.  Every time I go there I am always pleased with the waiting staff and they always make the experience that much more delightful.  The first time I went there I had their meatloaf, which some people either hear as "Ew" or some go "I only eat my mom\'s".  I do not want to knock any mother\'s out there, but this meatloaf was absolutely phenomenal!  Our server, Gary, recommended it to us and I\'ve never viewed meatloaf the same.  My boy, Gary and my boy Sam are both super legit and just awesome servers, you should ask to sit in their sections.  I usually look forward to off menu items as well after getting an off menu lamb shank.  For those looking to start the meal off right you must go with the Original Chopped Salad.  It is mind blowing!!  Also for those looking for a vice, my drink of choice is the Import which is Jameson with Port, Guinness Foam and Tobacco Bitters, I make sure to always get that every time I go.  Citizen will not disappoint, if you are visiting and have no idea where to eat, you must eat here.  I make sure to always bring out of towners to Citizen for a good meal.\n\nCheers!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-01-28', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Hch2Ut2vZ3P8YKGkeEjI-Q', 'review_id': '7oBPtGaqat3gshmxNWkywg', 'text': 'Ended up here after trying to go to Citizen R+D.  We ended up sitting in the bar area on a high top. They offer a good selection of wine by the glass and had the Crush Cab, which was very good. Not sure if the bar menu is different than the main room menu, but the selections seemed rather limited. \nWe ended up going with the Lamb Burger and Original Chop salad. Both were very good. The wait staff was attentive and friendly,', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-01-28', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '9eOdcbScYDPWnC0L2iRpmg', 'review_id': 'eCK93wRIJqsRf04COSO33g', 'text': 'Great location.  Food was good. Loved the bacon popcorn. Some very tasty interesting drinks.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-01-29', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '_CZEVp2gAryC41auedsREw', 'review_id': 'yFp-oIuwOj9SRQr9bINkZA', 'text': 'Mostly everything was great! Great service and our main dishes were great. We had the truffle grilled cheese and trout with quinoa So good! Only giving them four stars because our fondue appetizer was super watery :( Our meat and cheese plate was much better.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-02-03', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'bIfe59TmOENFc2YC2B-aHQ', 'review_id': '76VgRgk9cEJPgwCgc5AtEg', 'text': 'Enjoyed this one. \n\nThe chopped salad is pushed pretty hard but well worth it. I stated it was very similar to Cowboy Ciao only to find the chef worked there for 14 years. Still, very yummy. \n\nI ordered the osso buco.  Out of this world!  I was full, but wanted more. Going to go back to try more specials. \n\nServer was terrific. Recommend reservations.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-02-03', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'V9ApFr5rtxI8Te81BiUJiw', 'review_id': '3pxbAbC5B6VCSf8tsKVsqw', 'text': 'This place has been in business for 5 years now and not sure why it took me so long to try it.  The staff is friendly and helpful.  \n\nThe menu offers many temptations and while I enjoy an entree I did not stick to the typical dining.   While they offer appetizers, salads, entrees and more they also offer a variety of small plates.  We ordered 6 different small plates.  Each were very tasty, especially the eggplant dish!\n\nI look forward to dining again soon at this Old Town Scottsdale gem!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-03', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'UyOxTk77e2lSpY5XR_5qJw', 'review_id': 'wnj9Ce1xyYHatcB6FSXZPg', 'text': 'Food is f-ing amazing the atmosphere the bartenders are nice the servers act like actually care about you. What more could you ask for. Great place for a first date and then hit old town.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-04', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'pUG7tOChmXc_fn_-QEIPNw', 'review_id': 'yCkFkXv7oVC_UJizErpDvA', 'text': 'The bomb.com\nLoved it! Perfect portions, delicious food, and fun drink options!!! I will definitely be back soon.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-02-04', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 2, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '16ore4BzhF3XCa9OpDFE5g', 'review_id': 'B1Z6D4ThApSelGSjhUJyng', 'text': "Visiting Scottsdale as I'm used to I wanted to try something new. New at least to me. I was staring at a hotel near this place and the reviews couldn't be better, but what really made me decide was the pictures showing a very unique kitchen.\nAs I arrived the place was packed but traveling by myself has its advantages I was able to find a place at the bar.\nThis guys are friendly and even though the bar was full, the service was excellent.\nStarted with a glass of wine and the crab cakes. They arrive within 5 minutes oil ordered them. Taste was fresh and not fishy at all, loved how well they go with the salad and sauce they came on top of. They tastes very good but I am sure there has to be another appetizer in the menu that would actually blow my mind. Not a bad start at all\n\nTo follow the trout: presentation was a 10, cooked to perfection with skin as it should. The flavor as good and perfect it was, also it was also missing something, I was set up to be impressed but I was stopped just just short of it. \n\nAs good as the appetizer and the entree were I would not repeat these dishes as it is my believe there has to be a mind blowing dish... Maybe the scallops ? \n\nTo finish the bread pudding... It actually has bacon on it!! STOP THE PRESS!!! I've found it!! One out of three. This is just fantastic and mind blowing. apple and bacon bread pudding with brown butter ice cream is TO DIE FOR!\n\nThis gives solid grounds to my theory that there has to be other mind blowing items in the menu I have not tried.\n\nThis is a very solid 4 star restaurant, I just need my mind blown 3 out 3 but being so close to do so I will definitely give this restaurant a try", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-02-05', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': '1aol7aV71Dx8H6N8u2doRA', 'review_id': 'wYfAyoihA0-eRJt6m4HLLA', 'text': 'Best joint in Scottsdale.  Eat here. Often.  Unique.  Great service. The best. Great dessert. Great everything. Inventive cocktails.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-13', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'AdxydgO5Esau8RHb3SFIJw', 'review_id': 'qNuOnlxxlaLS7L-1CJfc-w', 'text': "Once again a great experience. The fixed menu for Valentine's Day was wonderful and the service is the best.\n\nThe scallops were so good....in fact, Ber I've ever had. The were buttery but the bacon and grits really evened out the sea saltiness! The julep hit the spot but was a little minty.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-14', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'fH8ls0onIwa7kCmyPfOSsg', 'review_id': '4ger-LlbHqmnLo1Orpe9nQ', 'text': u"An absolutely amazing Valentine's Day menu. Great staff, very quick service, wonderful drinks, food that will blow the taste buds right out of your mouth. Second in the Valley only to Caf\xe9 Monarch (although prices and happy hour are better)...and not by much! Thanks for a perfect evening!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-14', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'EGiAtB4sgZhDdYpRkDneig', 'review_id': 'ns85sWycnHKYs7TJ_FBpPA', 'text': "Part of my Hubby's Valentine's surprise was bringing me here for dinner. It was perfect from start to finish! Our waiter was wonderful!! It was a set menu, I chose the chia tuna as my 1st and my Husband (JB) had the chop, both were amazing! I LOVED the chop!  JB loved the tuna! My second was the scallops, and it was up there as one of the best plates I have had. JB had the filet and it was good, but not amazing.  I noticed it had that same sauce as the meatloaf from when I was first here. I just don't think the taste is fitting to the dish.  Then dessert, the caramel sauce made the red velvet perfect and the flourless chocolate cake was so great! I think the texture made it the best!! Beyond rich! Soooo good! I look forward to another visit for sure! Maybe happy hour, I love a budget gourmet feast, the $170 tab for tonight was a little much, but very much worth it. It was the perfect way to end our romantic day!  Side note ... Thank you/sorry (what ever fits) to the fellow diners that had the deal with our loving affectionate way of dining... The feeding each other and kissing constantly is how we roll... :P  I love you SBM!! Thank you for an amazing Valentine's day!!!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-14', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'pnBbtog75YNx5XhVij5HRw', 'review_id': 'Ig-tMX58-z3PapbgwPcvvg', 'text': 'We sat at the bar for happy hour food was amazing .... Service exceptional . A must try for your taste buds.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-16', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'ENACzrJySEh-Wb7xlSvuDw', 'review_id': '_R64rzGSuhZoURdg9ESYvg', 'text': 'I have been to Scottsdale many times over a period of 16 years, and I live in the NYC area. As such, my standards are very high, and many times I was disappointed by what many said were "good" restaurants in Scottsdale. I know that sounds arrogant, but the truth is when one is used to top shelf Michelin rated restaurants, one has high standards. That being said, Citizens Public House meets the high quality of New York City. \n\nFirst, the Negroni is the best I ever had. I have had Negroni in the SoHo House, Mas Farmhouse, Four Seasons Restaurant, and Le Cirque in Manhattan and Florence, Italy, which is the birthplace of the Negroni, and Citizen Public House beats them all. What did they do better? They aged the drink in barrels. It was the smoothest Negroni I ever had. The pork belly was THE best I ever had. It was not fatty and no gristle. The chopped salad was spectacular. The lamb burger was amazing - flavor bursted in my mouth with each bite. \n\nThere are no words to describe how good this restaurant is. Moreover, I was there while my father was dying in hospice. I took my mother here to get our minds off of our terrible situation. The staff was beyond extremely polite. caring and courteous. They were superb. You will not do better than Citizen Public House!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-17', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'cCwj4RJSKU4-o9ZZ1VTtmA', 'review_id': 'pg5AHK7Ly1mfQHkTfpXGzg', 'text': "The food is fantastic, and the staff is very friendly.  We sat outside on the patio during the perfect evening.  We wouldn't change anything about the place.  Definitely recommend the popcorn, fondue and house salad.  All photo and news worthy!  Go try this place out now!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-18', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'pOim-Tccfc6Aw0ynGdPmYw', 'review_id': '3zvxqkIO4gow6Rete81Svw', 'text': "Tried for the first time tonight, and was not disappointed by anything we ordered.  The meatloaf and short ribs were awesome and I was told that the scallops were the best in town ( I don't eat fish, but wife assured me).  Bread pudding for dessert was devine.  We will be back many times", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-18', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'WO9MS1xEJL4vb54ig_YW5Q', 'review_id': '-7taiMXayyv8GwbHRO46HA', 'text': 'I wasn\'t as impressed as others by Citizen Public House and I really wanted to be.  It was good, but not great.  Had the chopped salad and it was full of flavor, but didn\'t leave me wanting more.  In fact, we stopped ordering after it and left before we had a meal.  I can\'t put my finger on exactly any one thing, but didn\'t feel inclined to stay.  The waitress lacked culinary instincts and seemed interested to "sell" rather than guide us to what would interest us.  Overall, I wouldn\'t come back with all the other amazing options in old Scottsdale.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-02-19', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 4, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'pBtKerBCIX6JRh5q9N7ifw', 'review_id': 'LMsCQcx1aBEtCJxxHxAQxw', 'text': 'We arrived late and the place was packed so we decided to eat at the bar. Waitress was nice and friendly. Place was hopping\n\nStarted out my dinner with a Manhattan. Excellent drink and the smoky / citrus overtones of the drink were a great marriage.\n\nOrdered the Pork Osso Buco for dinner. This was the only let down of the night. While the pork had a nice flavor, the meat was cold near the bone (so I could tell it had been  pre-cooked) and the mashed potatoes were pretty flavorless. \n\nFollowed up dinner with a Guinness beer. Got to give it to the bartenders, they looked like they were having a blast. Kind of guys I would love to hire for my business.\n\nWhile my overall rating was a 3 (based primarily on the food) if I am back in town I will be glad to give the place a second chance.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-02-23', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'YDgxOWa7wqq_VSx6mOpu1g', 'review_id': 'lZ8qF492F4AG300xfr7BGg', 'text': 'Stopped by for a pre dinner cocktail... great experience. The cocktails were fresh and interesting (e.g. Thai Margarita and a homemade Vodka blend).  Staff were friendly and helpful, inclduing giving us some great Scottsdale recommendations.\nFood looked good and will try next time', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-02-25', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'VNIEGhjE2rMBD-ZdhY94-Q', 'review_id': 'O8vL3sTy-jeRYSQnC5NHOA', 'text': "This restaurant /bar is in a nice location in old town Scottsdale . The food is always delicious and the servers are great and up beat. Our favorite is Sam he is very knowledgable in regards to the food and cocktails and gives great recommendations. It can be difficult to have a good conversation as it gets pretty loud towards later in the evening when the bar fills up. It's dim lighting , candles, and white table cloths gives it a nice feel. Enjoy", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-02-25', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 2, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'r0NV8zDQgvlUUXB7AKtS-Q', 'review_id': 'dBcKwSfuZ-vdm5GE9VHAjg', 'text': 'This was one of those places that was fascinating to experience, and you don\'t know if you should document the evening chronologically, or by vice to virtue (or vice versa).\n\nI love that my girl servin\' us encouraged me to try somethin\' new-- the Import. Ultimately, it didn\'t work out, and she struck it from the check (despite my protests) and stood behind the joint\'s penchant for gettin\' fools open on food. Integrity = respect.\n\nIt was actually a rad conversation, because at first I couldn\'t come down on how I felt about this Jameson, tobacco bitters, tawny port & Guinness foam concoction, but I landed on "It tastes like a flat Old Fashioned," and gettin\' there was a few interactions between she-beaux and I and my girl servin\' it up. That meant no pretense, no chit-chat, just real-talk about food and experience.\n\nIronically, my love had a drink called the Pleasantville that she described as "boring."\n\nWhile the pork was dry on the outside, it was tasty and moist internally, and the polenta was a bit scarce, but equally tasty. She-beaux destroyed the scallops, and the tuna that set the meal off was way off the meat rack.\n\nFinally, the atmosphere (or crowd): we could not tear our eyes away from the desert rose (the Sweet Dee kind) who was way out of this homeboy\'s league, him with his jeans and flip flops and checked shirt tucked in (no belt(!)) and cuffs rolled up just once--- just once, mind you! This little scene was par for the course.  \n\nBut my man sealed the deal, much to our bewilderment, and I think the Citizen\'s contribution to this feat shouldn\'t be underestimated or understated.\n\nWhat else could explain such a thing?\n\nLoved this place. Absolutely loved it.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-02-28', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'XNfzsYAuI2rWDAvz_9Ja9w', 'review_id': 'Lxso7nopXiXu65EtipVwQQ', 'text': 'Was eating with my sister that has to eat gluten free and there are many options to choose from!  Everything was delicious and service was excellent.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-01', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'VEQ6P_wJTfaS-vnHAcWXCw', 'review_id': 'Y7vdD3Fj1gO08kft_AYjeQ', 'text': 'A memorable meal!  A server at a local bar recommended we try the ahi, chopped salad and scallops.  All were perfect!   The scallops were done to perfection, and the flavors were incredible!  Service was also top notch, and we felt with the service and good food, we had one of the best meals ever!  I look forward to a return visit.  \n\nIf only more restaurants could learn from Citizen Public House!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-03', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'jFHmCsK5Vs3qSS5vvmb2Jw', 'review_id': 'osQJgj5DrbIjmW_2gWnm1Q', 'text': "What a cool place! It's an upscale pub and refreshingly versatile. If you wanted to come with a few friends and have bar food, it's great. If you want to come with a big group, it's a fun, loud atmosphere. But somehow there is something very romantic about it - I'm not sure if its the dim candle-lit mood or the way that you just feel in your own world, but you can have a very intimate dinner right in the middle of it all and not even notice.\n\nThe food is delicious!! I had the BEST GRILLED CHEESE ever. High quality cheese and bread, and white truffle scented mashed potatoes! Mmmmmmmm. The crabcakes are delicious and the short ribs were excellent! The catfish was also delicious but it's pretty spicy, so be aware. It's a little on the pricier side, but you're in the middle of downtown Scottsdale with great ambiance and very good food. Definitely makes for a special night. \n\n4.5 stars so I'll round up!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-04', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '5RRFgTn5CeVCrdRkW8ks9g', 'review_id': 'FGHJ7UpZPnYQeLms_hOyqg', 'text': 'I love this place and have been back many times.  Great food and great atmosphere.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-03-05', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 6, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'vEwO-cbAQy3tRUepzmyczA', 'review_id': 'lOlW04XwTAPRtYnBFrWpIw', 'text': 'Let me start off by saying we were pretty excited to try this place, especially since a few of us even had this bookmarked on yelp... \n\nBut damn this place is dissappointing.  \n\nA bunch of us are in town for Spring Training and tried to hit up Citizen Public House.  The place wasn\'t too packed... more open tables than filled tables.  \nWe showed up at around 10:30 on Saturday night walked up to the hostess and told her we had a party of seven.  She confidently told us "Sure, just a few moments", looked us all up and down then walked away into the back.  \nA couple minutes later, she comes back and says "Sorry, we can\'t seat 7 people right now."\n\n......  Seriously???  WTF?!?!?!\n\nWe asked about all the empty tables and she said we can\'t sit there.\n\nI\'m assuming they didn\'t want to seat us because we were slightly dressed down (even though attire shows \'casual\') or because we weren\'t a group of the standard middle aged white dudes in button shirts, jeans and dress shoes.\n\nwhatever the case is, it came off as a kind of pompous place with a hostess (or manager) who looks down on people.\n\nYou guys missed out on a few hundred dollars plus a big tip from us.... not that you care though.\n\n***this review is soley based on service since we never got the chance to eat here***', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 1, 'date': '2015-03-08', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'tZBkURtI92L-rLqO15TWjg', 'review_id': 'ZxzMIWwiqfeTJNuIaDq1dg', 'text': 'Great place, awesome atmosphere, food + drinks rock. Make sure to get their famous salad!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-08', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'U2rM4xmb_mQKeJ_1OmnJ5w', 'review_id': 'PeU4xsjgU_5SFI6NxlI_Ag', 'text': 'We had a great meal - I would go back in a heartbeat.  I reccomend the pork osoboko', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-10', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'qhuiYov7UwAPDibrlg_Cbw', 'review_id': 'RlJ1ZQVjXy3NUdhE3BtB2Q', 'text': "This is a solid restaurant. I've been here twice and enjoyed it both times. The food is delicious and the service is rock solid. I've had the scallops both times I've eaten there. Good presentation and tasty dish all around. \nThe wine list is impressive not in quantity but in quality. A nice selection of different wines for different tastes. My dad had a Manhattan and he said it was the best he's ever had. And he's drunk a lot of Manhattans over his life. \n\nWhen I came here the first time, the server messed up on my friend's order. When notified right away about the mistake, the server said that our table could keep the mistake dish and the actual order will be out right away. It showed up five minutes later and the server was apologetic. Nothing over the top but apologetic. He ended up not charging our table for either of the dishes. Completely unexpected and appreciated. He got a good tip. \n\nI deducted one star because the the noise level inside is very high. The restaurant has concrete floors and drywall. The only thing soaking up the sound is people's clothes. It's hard to have intimate conversations since it's so loud inside.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-03-15', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Q2sEnEfW5KCayQISuFYj4A', 'review_id': 'qB5Zy84y1kYPn7ZaR2MBZQ', 'text': 'Let\'s talk about a really good dining experience that was brought down by a HORRIBLE HOSTESS. We were in the area after some shopping at the mall close by and decided to check out this restaurant after doing some research on Yelp. We arrived around 8:15pm and requested a table for 3. The asian hostess, Stacey, snubbed us and told us that there was a 2 hour wait. We did not really have a problem with that since it was a Saturday night and the restaurant appeared busy. However, I decided to hop on Open Table to see if there were any reservations available. Low and behold, there was an 8:45, 9:00, 9:15... reservation for 3 available. We decided to reserve the 8:45pm reservation and hang out til our time was up....\n\nWe returned to the restaurant at 8:45pm and let the hostess know that we had a reservation. Again, SNUBBED BY STACEY and surprise, there was a table available for us! We were shocked at how she did not seem to care that she told us that there was a 2 hour wait when we were able to reserve a table for 30 minutes later...\n\nBeyond the horrible waitress, I would rate this restaurant 4 stars.  Our waiter AJ was amazing. He should get 5+ stars He was friendly, had great recommendations and was very attentive to our needs. Everyone that served us was friendly and super attentive!\n\nThe food was 4 stars. We enjoyed the following items:\n- The Bacon Fat Heirloom Popcorn -- This was probably the most disappointing dish we had. There were hints of bacon fat but it needed some kind of kick like an herb to make it pop?\n- The Original Chopped Salad -- Apparently it has it\'s own Facebook page. It\'s definitely worth the hype! It\'s similar to a tea salad at a burmese restaurant in the way it is presented.\n- Buttermilk Chicken -- The chicken was juicy throughout.\n- Pork Osso Buco -- Fall off the bone good.\n- Pan Seared Scallops -- Recommended by our waiter and was delicious! \n\nOverall, I would\'ve rated this place 4 stars had it not been for our horrible hostess situation... so it\'s gets bumped down to 3 stars. To add insult to injury, I also want to add that I just received an email from Open Table stating that I "No Showed" for our reservation. I guess Stacey once again reiterated how much she didn\'t want us there...', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-03-15', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'RJp2Ctwa8RzlzT_tcloquA', 'review_id': '8HoilKtql-aN-mVYujejbw', 'text': "Wow. Wow wow!!!\nThe hostess' were able to get 5 of us in on a busy Saturday night without a reservation.. WOW! I was so excited to go here and when I found out they were fully committed that night, I could have cried. BUT the hostess came to our rescue and were able to squeeze us in and I almost started crying again! Obviously, a happy cry moral of that story, make a reservation. Like at least two days in advance.\n\nThe food was phenomenal and so was the service. Our server, Sam, really took care of us. He was knowledgable, kind, funny and definitely ordered for us only because we asked him to. \nWe had so many different items, but the one that stuck out the most was that chopped salad with salmon. I can seriously have one every single day and never get tired of it (ok maybe I'm reaching a little, but still, SO GOOD!)\nI want to come back to Scottsdale just for this place. So, I just might!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-18', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': 'paUB8cUiC_6aBS8ktBoTDg', 'review_id': 'eV-KtH0TIbKNH-E1FLCroA', 'text': 'The salad is probably one of the best I have ever eaten. Layers upon layers of fresh vibrant flavor. Excellent ambiance. Perfect place for a date.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-03-18', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '7--UNhd8jumkF3b0eC93cQ', 'review_id': 'TekXsHt7ieDgvVxUxzWOqQ', 'text': "Really love the decor and outdoor porch here. We walked there without a reservation and got lucky a table outside was available. It was also pretty late in the night. So my coworker and I sat under the stars warmed by the heat lamp and started ordering some wine and cocktails and started with their popular salad. Oh man.. it totally reminds me of a tea salad when the waitress explains all the parts and mix them together. The salad was just absolutely delicious and was a great starter. I then got the short ribs (rubbed with coffee), so I definitely couldn't resist that. The short ribs was so tender, I didn't need to use the knife they gave me. I wasn't a huge fan of the parsnip puree, but it was very smooth.\nMy coworker's pork osso buco was also super tender and juicy. This place has a great vibe and great for hanging out with friends.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-19', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'roUn40O59FXKANgtwpZ6mA', 'review_id': 'WzTl-NK3PIVhliL7w9t_jA', 'text': 'I\'ve been wanting to try this restaurant since we\'ve had a sampling tasting at the Devoured Culinary Festival. We came here for our Anniversary (wanted a place different and trendy). We booked our reservation on Open Table. We were seated right away, water poured , Katie our server introduced herself and wished us a Happy Anniversary right off.\n\nWe started off with Cocktails: Manhattan and a Thai Margarita, both were very good. We opted to make a meal and share appetizers so we can taste a variety of dishes. We started with the "special" Uni Shooter, not a typical shooter style, the piece of uni was a good size but was overwhelmed by the Asian pear mushroom compo. We then moved onto The Original Chopped Salad (corn, couscous, smoked salmon, asiago, pepitas, tomatoes, arugula, currants, buttermilk pesto dressing) and the Pork Belly Pastrami (rye spaetzle, Brussels sprout sauerkraut, mustard jus). Both dishes were excellent. We then had the Chia Seared Tuna (Thai purple sticky rice, asparagus puree, fried leek & micro green salad) and the Deep Sea Red Crab Cakes (smoked re pepper aioli & celery root slaw), we both felt the tuna was good but the asparagus puree was odd and weak. The crab cakes were excellent. We ended the night with Katie delivering a wonderful complimentary Anniversary desert of a Chocolate Cake with Ice Cream topped with the best Carmel sauce I\'ve ever had and a sprinkle of the bacon popcorn.\n\nAtmosphere was very nice and trendy, service was excellent "thank you Katie!", food and drink were very good. A restaurant that is a must try.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-03-20', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Wh3wWbm007aKANG-wr2CcQ', 'review_id': 'ORzopuCRnQzHGlnSG2ghFA', 'text': 'My girlfriends and I came here for my bachelorette dinner and I\'m so glad we did! We flew into Scottsdale from Houston for a few days and loved the restaurant scene here! Citizen Public House was absolutely amazing!\n\nWe true the pork belly pastrami, chopped salad and I had the scallops for my entree.  Everything was absolutely DELICIOUS! We did a bit of research regarding the menu here before our dinner and originally thought, "A chopped salad? Really? How much better can it be than the ones served everywhere else?".  Boy, were we wrong! It was so worth it!  The pork belly pastrami was TO DIE FOR (ignore the fact that your cholesterol may shoot 50 points)! Hehe ;) The scallops were cooked perfectly and seasoned just right.  \n\nOur server was very knowledgable about the menu offerings and even suggested a few areas around town that we might like to visit after our dinner.  He was super friendly and checked on us frequently throughout the night.  \n\nIf I ever make a trip to Scottsdale again, I\'ll definitely be stopping by here again :)', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-20', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'gYpdCZzDD89UO9zrfFhl4A', 'review_id': 'GPss8uwuGPFzMw10wDpsvw', 'text': 'If you like over priced food and tiny portions this is the place for you. Sure the ambience is nice. The staff is friendly. The service is fine. But I\'m a gosh dang man and I need to fill my belly. I\'m not a fan of a cocky Cheff in the kitchen drizzling his special sauces all over my plate just so it can look fancy and he can jip me on my portion size in the name of gourmet. Honestly the flavors don\'t blow my mind either. We paid $28 for a scallop "entree" that came with 3 scallops and some overly cooked spinach and of course Cheff drizzles. If you\'re a wine-o and get a bit tipsy before hand you should be fine. Call me uncultured, maybe I don\'t fit the Scottsdale mold, but I won\'t be returning. Tonight this citizen has been let down by the public house.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 1, 'date': '2015-03-21', 'type': 'review'}
