{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'hQnDet_XvsW_0eTF4-qhlw', 'review_id': 'bAb_aXB74R78Gmnp0tYvpQ', 'text': 'This place is extremely loud but we sat outside on the front patio and that solved the problem.  The female server was top notch and unpretentious.  I would recommend the fondue as an appetizer, easily serving 2 or more. I had the meatloaf and it may be the best I ever had.  My wife had the asian beef wraps and loved them.  With the appetizer these were more than we could finish.  The drinks are expensive and my wife was underwhelmed with her designer cocktail.  I stuck to Guiness.  Overall we had a wonderful time and would recommend this place to anyone.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-24', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'DFAYwNpDnvgwuGnESRu3eA', 'review_id': 'IBehm8qOcgaeymD5U7HQKQ', 'text': "Nice atmosphere, classy but not snobby -- we had just gotten off a plane and they (kindly) didn't blink at our jeans and tshirts. One of the few places in Scottsdale open after 9. Appetizers were good, not great, but redeemed by the lamb burgers, which were the best we've ever had - juicy, perfectly cooked, lots of flavor. Service was friendly but spotty (we asked for bread, none came; we had a loooonnnnggg wait for our entrees despite being one of only 4 tables). I think this is probably a 5-star place when humming on all cylinders.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-03-25', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Toyff-4pehVKu3XZ6xjZ1Q', 'review_id': 'uGcut-mZATvAjm27WGeaKA', 'text': "This place is unbelievable!  I was visiting AZ from DC and saw that it has 4.5stars with 900+ reviews, so I knew there had to be something special!\n\nThe atmosphere is very chill, has indoor and outdoor seating.  Service was great, the waiter explained everything on the menu with such detail and passion that I couldn't  wait to try everything.\n\nThe chop salad is a must, perfect texture and flavor, the corn and salmon harmonize together wonderfully.  Also, for starters, we got the Tuna...one word....AMAZING.  Large chunks of tuna, seared and seasoned perfectly.\n\nThe three of us had the short rib, filet mignon and the osso bucco.  I couldn't tell which one I liked more.  The meats were prepped and cooked like nothing I have seen before.  The flavor, texture and juiciness were to die for.  I honestly could not find one single thing wrong with anything they had there, and I am an anal type of guy.  \n\nI even enjoyed two Thai Margaritas, that were the perfect balance of flavor and alcohol.  If you are in Arizona, you have to go to this place at least once.  I wish they had one in DC, I would honestly eat there twice a week!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-25', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'dlf1PiM91URYDanIQxBzOQ', 'review_id': 'DpN5GP1-Z41dm6wZmdm2JQ', 'text': 'The restaurant was disappointing. It started off great when the hostess seated us - a party of 4- despite our reservation was made for the wrong day. They accommodated my special requests. Then the food came. The salads were good. So was soup. But the ahi starter was subpar - tasteless and stringy. The pork dish was boring and dull at 28$. The lamb was salty.  They need to make sure they live up to high standards or they will lose folks. We wont be back.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-03-28', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'hPDtvbIkai49K1kYj7lfWQ', 'review_id': 'Jno2vyMsl6mjKn1kwPnC0w', 'text': "We went for my wife's birthday with another couple. We had a great time. The service was excellent. The food was really good with a varying selection of different tastes that played on comfort food.  The atmosphere was really happening. Not very quite or romantic, but a good place to party with a group.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-28', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '4YzfkW6uY7x5AF30_wYsAw', 'review_id': 'wdStOxsDPnTEqyAKS_KIog', 'text': 'Delicious.  The grilled cheese with mashed potatoes and bacon was wonderful.  Also was pleasantly surprised at the bacon popcorn.  It made me realize I have been eating popcorn wrong for years; all popcorn should have bacon.  Atmosphere and service were also wonderful.  Go for happy hour as they have some great deals on their food and drinks.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-29', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Amraq5ai5Fyna-gbuna1-A', 'review_id': 'Ui4OfONXZDhPmylYprBZRw', 'text': 'Great dinner spot in Scottsdale AZ, and with 900+ reviews, we knew it was a must try spot.  Came here for business and with friends and had a great time.  \n\nThe food and drinks were great, and the service was awesome.  I ordered the Pork Osso Buco.  The portion was "Fancy Restaurant" size, but every bit was flavorful and satisfying.  \n\nGreat spot to have a dinner meeting, not too loud and given great service by the staff.  The restaurant is located in a great convenient location where you can walk to various other restaurants or bars.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-30', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': 'bXRT4oZ6tlpOtJxpwxpHJg', 'review_id': 'ECK8YP3aDvndgxNIa23AXg', 'text': "Definitely one of the better restaurants in the Phoenix area. The food and service were excellent. I made a reservation for a large group and they gave us our own little alcove to sit in and we had a server all to ourselves. His name was Sean and he did a fantastic job.\n\nThe drinks were wonderful. I had a Tin Cup and a Liberator Punch. The Punch was better than the Tin Cup but they were both really good. I enjoy sweeter drinks but my husband had Manhattan and said it was great.\n\nFor dinner, I had the steelhead trout. The pickled beet salad with it was very good and the fish was cooked perfectly. I'd love to find out what they seasoned the fish with because it was perfect. My husband had the meatloaf and let me try a bite and it was very tasty. My friend had the scallops and she let me try a bit of the grits and she's lucky I didn't snatch the plate away from her. I'm wondering if they'd just sell me some of those grits.\n\nI also managed to mooch bites of the infamous Original Chopped Salad (which is really pretty before they toss it all together) and the short ribs. Both were excellent.\n\nFor dessert, my husband and I split a Pig in the Orchard which is bread pudding with apple and bacon. A most excellent combination. We also took home a bag of the Pecan Bacon Brittle which is as awesome as it sounds.\n\nI definitely plan to go back and have my own plate of grits, um, scallops.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-03-30', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 2, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '_ccE1msZJFhSVc0JLX0UmQ', 'review_id': 'tn-lnDGSKI0-Wnoj4Zf3oQ', 'text': "The best chopped salad. I mean it has its own facebook page. Idk if its the texture, the dressing, or the quality and freshness of the salad ingredients, but it's the best. Just thinking about it makes me want it. If i were to revisit Scottsdale, Arizona this may be the first spot i go to or the only spot i go to. Not only for their salad but also for their scallops with grits and pork belly pastrami. Citizen Public House delivers with ambiance, service, and obviously delicious food. Looking around at what the other tables ordered and from what our server had said each dish they offer is a customer favorite (and each table either had exactly what we had on our table or other dishes we thought of getting) and I believe him. Each dish we had was rich with flavor, seasoned perfectly, and just melds perfectly at each bite.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-04-02', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'JprN2pQ8b95fDo8eGpMK3g', 'review_id': 'iUaHPeIc4Hjh4QP0bJXJdA', 'text': "Great vibe for a nice dinner or casual meet up. I'm giving 4 stars because the happy hour was a bit formal for my taste. The drinks and food were spot on and you will not be disappointed. The staff must get some great training - they all are very polite and super responsive. I had everything on the happy hour menu, their Negroni and 2 of their other drink specials that were very, very well mixed.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-04-02', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'pZIWbtC6x0CGvxL-ln8m2A', 'review_id': 'J3WmuxmGW08qpmaI0Lf9FA', 'text': "Loved this place! The ambiance was great and the servers were super friendly and helpful. Really liked that the indoor to outdoor seating was an open floor plan, made the place look larger and more welcoming. \n\nThey have a great HH! We started with the meat/cheese plate for only $6 and it was a good sized portion for 2. Also had some wine which was also great for $5. For our main course, the chopped salad was terrific. Very different than most chopped salads I've had but it was great. My boyfriend had the roasted pork and he said it was good but a tad dry.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-04-02', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'rMdKdaRw242jHhnAMrfxEg', 'review_id': 'NaXNTgTv6CCtT5go3KzmwA', 'text': "Decided to branch out while we were in Scottsdale, and hubs wanted to try this place.  I okay'd it based on Yelpers.  Front of house staff were so kind and accommodating, and the service didn't end there.  Bradley - thank you for all your suggestions.  You perfectly timed the courses, helped with the wine decision, and were simply great.\n\nWhen I looked at the menu a Chopped Salad was listed so I asked.  Turns out the chef at CPH was the chef at Cowboy Ciao who developed the Chopped Salad.  As far as we could discern both salads were identical and equally delicious.  Hubs and I shared the Scallops and Buttermilk Chicken.  Scallops were perfectly seared and served over corn grits w/bacon that were the lightest I've ever eaten.  The boneless chicken - difficult to cook and not dry out - was so tender and moist, served with Brussels sprouts and succotash, a great combo over the typical (or what I serve) mashed potatoes.  \n\nThe only negative I would add is that this place is LOUD, and could definitely use some noise mitigation.  \n\nAbsolutely no room for dessert, we waddled back to our hotel.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-04-02', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '04JYBbdJe-JIurHDRQW1Lg', 'review_id': 'gdycXbzw3oDTMwdqb5Bm8A', 'text': 'Happy Hour fondue, sliders & wine-all were great & and ranged in price from $4.5 to $6. Service was excellent. Fondue was accompanied by bread, pears and sausage, oh my!  Wished I had room to try the crab cakes that sounded delish.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-04-03', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'JYsWgYEt8e33iDYHcm-qlQ', 'review_id': 'T4Gfbzx8XCGdwvsLe1hH-g', 'text': "Came in about 5pm, sat down right away. Brad, my waiter came over and introduced himself and asked me my name. I'd seen yelp reviews so told him they sounded good. Brad and the staff checked on me several times to make sure I was good even though the place was busy. AMAZING food and atmosphere. Highly recommended.  I'll be back for sure!!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-04-03', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'lOkmVTHhuijgIR5fNHamDQ', 'review_id': 'prNNxZzOftYtnhQN9MbjpQ', 'text': u"Yum!  My husband and I chose to eat here the other night and we depended on yelp reviews since we are from out of town.  All I can say is the yelp reviews are accurate.  I had the pork osso bucco and it was amazing!  The meat was fall off the bone tender and juicy.  The pork was sitting on delicious polenta and had a sauce reduction along with an accent of deeply roasted tomatoes and perfectly cooked kale.  \n\nMy husband had the short ribs with parsnip pur\xe9e that he really enjoyed but I really can't comment on them since I didn't have any.  They looked delicious and I know he really loved them.\n\nThis is not an inexpensive place but we felt the quality was definitely there.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-04-03', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '4-tLIRDItfpsO5TsI-KHeQ', 'review_id': 'lddrxBnK8yKtPgR1ZI7dYQ', 'text': 'Absolutely amazing!! My husband and I wanted a nice restaurant with good food for our last night visiting Scottsdale. This place was perfect!! Our waiter Shawn was very knowledgable about the menu and a pleasure to talk to. The filet mignon and the scallop dishes are to die for! They also have a great wine list. The place has a very hip yet romantic feel to it and is great for a date night!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-04-06', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'HvvDcxDywBkRQjXsgwsXDQ', 'review_id': 'gkTj13Lym5BhOJdQ6tOCyg', 'text': "The service was great but while I'm almost always happy with the special - the veal wasn't that great - merely ok.  Our waitress and the supporting  servers were always attentive but unobtrusive.  The fondue and olive appetizers were great and the old fashioned I had and the manhattan my father in law had were tasty.  The wife's filet and my father in laws scallops were well prepared as were the kids meals (off menu) but I was rather let down by the veal special... I would chalk it up to a minor miss in an otherwise fantistic dinner expericne.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-04-07', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 't4iPJB45b6I9jbGHcbk6Ow', 'review_id': '9dHtnuXagcGqvMVIjBkYUw', 'text': "Visited Citizen at the end of March while in town for a few days of spring break. Dined with local friends who suggested it. Had a wonderful meal. The bacon popcorn as an appetizer was a definite hit. Ditto for the Pork Belly Pastrami. DO NOT pass up the chopped salad - an unusual combination of ingredients that was delicious. All six of us were very pleased with our choices, which inckuded meatloaf, trout, crab cakes, filet or osso buco. Good wine selection. (Specials during happy hour.). One of us made an interesting observation: there was no salt and pepper on the table. But they weren't needed, since everything was seasoned perfectly. Alas, we had no room for dessert. One final comment: AJ was the most solicitous and engaging waiter we've ever met.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-04-07', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'B4fmGBdMTs1EklmvTox8Tg', 'review_id': 'a6s1Xvkd6vkw_hTmLdIk3Q', 'text': "Yelp is a swindle!\nYou can give every review you want they choose them!\nDon't waste your time with this site!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-04-08', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'KeoPjzZldhjQq7rZPzWBrw', 'review_id': 'ewJV6yyO8lZN08bzmz79ag', 'text': 'Great place for a romantic get a way! Food and service were great! Only suggestion would be to expand on wines by the glass!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-04-08', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'Dl6nrttaXssRTccqgWAEKw', 'review_id': 'QHLUqtzj43uxkP7grmpOiQ', 'text': 'Loved the indoor/outdoor space & appreciated them accommodating our group of 6 with no reservation.  Popcorn with sizzling bacon was incredible. We had to order 2 bowls and I think I ate 1 almost entirely by myself. Meatloaf & my beautifully arranged chop salad were also amazing.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-04-08', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'apR9vUzu1OV-KjfeE_s7kw', 'review_id': 'mDrKe6gyOdhmW1tx4Gn_dg', 'text': 'This is a fantastic restaurant that I highly recommend for anyone in the Scottsdale area!\n\nLast week I hosted an event and it could not have gone any better.\n\nWhen setting up the event, the staff and in particular Stacie Ten Eyck were so helpful and accommodating. They went above and beyond to help with the set up.\n\nMoreover, the event itself was fabulous. The wine and beverage choices were fantastic, the food was divine and ambience was fun and sophisticated. \n\nWe had waiter by the name of Gary who kept the group entertained for the evening and truly made it a remarkable experience.\n\nI have since downloaded their recipe for their signature chopped salad which is fantastic! I only wish I lived in the area to go back.\n\nThis is a must in book for dining in Phoenix/Scottsdale!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-04-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'pFVuL2rpL0g4gi2V57DZTg', 'review_id': 'N1VsW60gOz1BFyr9-y0lTw', 'text': "I'll go here for a cocktail called The Import. Everything is amazing here- staff, food (famous chopped salad), atmosphere. Even being in the center of Old Town Scottsdale it doesn't get obnoxious. There are nights where they are jam packed- even around the bar. Plan ahead if you are going on a date.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-04-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'loBmwupSPmrxw7ST342PFg', 'review_id': 'hNUXMvKBXdy1Ak3UFZFTyg', 'text': "I came here the other evening for happy hour and ended up staying for dinner.\n\nI am very impressed! We ordered the crabcakes, which were light, fresh and tastey. They are deep friend but it didn't feel unhealthy or overly saturated in fat which was great. I ordered the scallops because of all the wonderful reviews on here, and yet again yelp did not fail me! My friend ordered the short rib, which was also excellent, I like how they serve the sauce on the side as to not over power it. One thing to note though: my scallop dish was very small (3 scallops) and my friend got two massive pieces of short rib. The portions were way off. I was still slightly hungry after my scallops and 1 crab cake, so of course we ordered the apple bacon bread pudding, which was nice. The blueberry sauce they put on it is great, not too sweet and compliments the other flavours nicely.\n\nThe ambiance is also very nice, with lots of light and fresh air coming in, crisp white tables clothes while still giving the allusion of being somewhat casual. \n\nThe cocktails were okay as well, the ones that we tried from the menu didn't amaze me. But weren't bad either, I'm rather picky admittedly. I did have the bartender make me an extra dirty martini which for once in Arizona was done almost perfectly. I don't know what is it with the desert but they can't make a martini to save their life. But here it was pretty good, I'll be returning for that. I should also note they have Sipsmith here! Haven't seen that in other bars in the area so I was very excited as that is my gin of choice.\n\nAll is all - nice place, good food, decent price, acceptable cocktails.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-04-10', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'cZiY0fEvKdaY9LvrMX0LsQ', 'review_id': 'QeWC00Omv_fz7VLUcav5_w', 'text': "Awful! The variety wasn't good and, besides that, their nasty chicken gave me food poisoning! I would strongly recommend to not go here!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 1, 'date': '2015-04-13', 'type': 'review'}
