{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'RBJqkgUxz11Y34SuXBd4uQ', 'review_id': 'TxjY2wZcPl9gOPi-coOyDw', 'text': 'Citizen was recommended by multiple people. ......plus Yelp had it rated very high......so Citizen it was...... we sat at the bar and Brendan was our server......he was very helpful with recommendations.......we made it there for happy hour and so we tried the hummus and pita plate......this was very good......then came the very highly acclaimed chopped salad. ......not expecting this.......it was totally different then anything I ever had........it was excellent. .......so far Brendan was 2 for 2......then came the scallops........they were excellently. ......a great choice......it must say......the service was excellent....the food was excellent and our total experience was excellent. .....it f you want to recommend a nice place with quality this is the place......good job Brendan.......', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-05', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 4, 'cool': 4}, 'user_id': 'L5e5_gNEA3N-B4swnYVLLA', 'review_id': 'JKYUXw8Xxri6r6UnpQXJNA', 'text': "I had high expectations for CPH. Great reviews, good menu and a hip vibe. \nI see the potential but unfortunately it didn't live up to expectations. \nFood: For starters we split The Original Chopped Salad. We weren't aware that it has Salmon mixed in it...and I cannot stand salmon...so I barely had it. My wife liked it though. Entrees - TRUFFLE GRILLED CHEESE (white truffle scented mashed potato, Emmental, melted onion, French bread, simple field greens) which was very oily and buttery. The bread was a little soggy and not toasted enough. FAIR TRADE SHORT RIBS (coffee rub, dried cherry bbq sauce,roasted parsnip puree & seasonal veg) did the job for my wife but I thought it was ok.  Dessert -  PEANUT BUTTER STRATA BAR\n(white chocolate ice cream, strawberry jam, peanut butter crunch) was eh. PB was flaky not creamy. \nAtmosphere - Loud and modern. \nService - Good, no complaints. The hostess did hook us up with a seat without having a reservation. We tugged on her heartstrings. \nPrices - Expensive. I am all for paying for a great meal but if you add a couple of drinks your dropping bucks here. \nI do admit if you want to go for a drink and be noticed, this a good place to go. Parking is bit tricky but we scored a spot a few steps away.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-05-06', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'BH6wxHHG0JdYeq5Uw0XU1g', 'review_id': 'xnzQIOj78KXjkVbx6gwbJQ', 'text': "I've been here twice for dinner,  once for a date and  again for a group dinner with friends. CPH has a great atmosphere for both. \nThe chopped salad is a must, and the scallops and short ribs are great entrees. The cocktails are crafty and delicious! Overall a good spot to visit, especially if you have friends or family in town.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-05-07', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '77arFouPNYb9t5TrYHDBNg', 'review_id': 'vWwU8eT8gYdAuWilv9Obgg', 'text': "My first dinner here a few years a go was wonderful, and  everything was delicious.  I had the chopped salad and scallops.  I went in March 2015 with some friends, and they were not impressed with their entrees.  The meat was overcooked, and they didn't think the scallops were as good a quality as they should have been for the price.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-05-07', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 5, 'useful': 12, 'cool': 8}, 'user_id': 'hLuKgo7G6us4wNQoFb7N8A', 'review_id': '_7eRSJOaJ2WnVh5ZiG9RuQ', 'text': 'Food like this exists?! In Scottsdale?! I think Scottsdale has better tasting food than San Diego! I saw Citizen on yelp and had my eye on it but was a bit tainted because my friend and I have bad experiences with "gastropubs" or at least the ones in Cali. It always turned out to be horrible tasting food that tries tooooo cool and overpriced... we took the leap of faith and said fck it lets do it, maybe Scottsdale gastropubs will be different, and indeed it was!\n\nWe couldn\'t get reservations (place is packed for a good reason) but the hostess said there were bar seats available, and we were cool with that. We just wanted food in and out. Also it was fight night, all the other bars were charging $20 each, why not spend that money on good food instead? \n\nI couldn\'t believe how good the food tasted here. I was in shocked because... well it\'s Scottsdale, wasn\'t sure if this was a foodie mecca. Citizen (and amongst other places) proved me wrong. We decided not to stuff our faces and instead get 2 apps and 1 entrees. \n-Chia Seared Tuna: the best seared tuna and most creative seared tuna I\'ve tried thus far...and I eat out a lot (1130+ reviews). The chia seeds were unique and gave it an amazing crunch! Put that with the asparagus puree, black-like rice and a spicy puree...it was a burst of flavors in your mouth. We licked the plate clean.\n-Crabcakes: For a landlock town, they sure weren\'t stingy on the crab meat! Every bit had crab and the breading was at a minimal so you actually tasted the crab!The aioli was also good on it but it was flavorful itself you probably didn\'t need it!\n-Pork Osso Buco: We usually have lamb, but pork is also a good alternative. The pork by itself is dry, but if you actually mix all the flavors it was not at all dry and had sooo many flavors. The polenta that tasted like butter and cheese with the roasted tomatoes and kale... it literally made my mouth melt and fall in love with this dish. The kale was cooked perfect! I can eat this everyday. \n\nEverything we had that night was excellent. This place sure was not the hype. Service was great, good was great, company was great... I think this is as good as it gets in Scottsdale for dinner... put this in SD and it\'ll be the new "it" restaurant. *Hint Hint* Come on over', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-07', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'n4Ro9p8Xd-AvWvXk5uYDcQ', 'review_id': '6YWfQvG8BaeSg6oy0nDUdg', 'text': '5 days in the Scottsdale area and this was our favorite dining experience for sure. Great energy, fresh and innovative dishes and great cocktails. Wait staff works hard!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 2, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'X1Pdz2CeI8ES_qPCIBd1vg', 'review_id': '0C4cJm_EBT52t11krBonTA', 'text': 'Food was burnt,  what else is there to say.  Nothing worse than horrible service and burnt food.  Spent $96 dollars total.  Next time I will buy steaks at Costco and call it a day.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 1, 'date': '2015-05-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'PJNyJ15UQQcq4Y3QLO7q2Q', 'review_id': 'PuCjbbbiI3Drhkr0j3jDlw', 'text': "as I got sick on vacation I was very upset that it went from exploring and eating around Scottsdale to me in bed nonstop, skip to 2 days later and the first thing I wanted to do was come here for my first real meal! our waiter was seriously the nicest waiter I've ever met and I have gone out to eat basically all over the world. whatever they are paying him should be doubled! \n\nanyway my grilled cheese was perfect for someone who hadn't eaten in 2 days and just so good. my husband loved his lamb burger, my mom wasn't a fan of hers but that's because she was expecting like fake lamb you'd get at like a mcdonalds or something lol. this is the real delicious lamb at this place :) I also loved the look of this place.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'M1EQRRC91pofvyUucOEmsw', 'review_id': 'rfbq0-5l30cBayWdnO-sdA', 'text': "4.5 stars.\n\nService:  Friendly, attentive, and helpful - this place did a great job of hiring a 5 star staff\n\nAtmosphere: Trendy, yet casual - you can pass with jeans, but I did see a couple tables that were pretty dressed up\n\nDrink: The Citi-Zen cocktail was a little on the sweet side, but still absolutely amazing\n\nFood: The pork belly pastrami and chopped salad were the highlights of the evening as they were both delicious. We also ordered the buttermilk chicken, which was good but nothing special, and the scallops, which were extremely salty - on the border of being inedible.\n\nOverall, even though Citizen didn't stand out enough to make this a 5 star review, it's still a great place to eat in the Scottsdale area.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-05-10', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'wCX1rcVAcB0d1XEB06VWlg', 'review_id': 'jGN27V7C-_pUA7OCPNt_7w', 'text': 'Welcomed by a friendly, attentive staff to a cool bar with inventive food that soars above "pub grub."  Bar bites were so good, we were challenged to choose and eat the main courses. Bites included the bacon-infused popcorn, fondue, olives, and rosemary-roasted mixed nuts. No wonder we weren\'t too hungry after that!  Ah, but then we enjoyed as main dishes:  chopped salad (unique and tasty), fried chicken, lamb burger, and grilled cheese sandwich. Alas, no room for dessert. Nice cocktail menu and wines by the glass.  Noise-level is pretty intense -- combination of music and acoustics -- making it hard to have a conversation and/or hear the server at times. Worth a visit in the 5th Avenue Shopping area.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-05-11', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 3, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': 'rz52Jd71PU9v2W8qa6H0Qg', 'review_id': 'ZLhfyQGo3hBRODnFuDb18Q', 'text': "Did not eat one thing that wasn't amazing (okay maybe the fries were the only thing just great).  I wish I lived closer so I could enjoy this place more often. My recommendations are: member's only drink, fondue (sausage is to die for!!), scallops, and the cheesecake. Steven (or Steve?) was great and made us feel appreciated and special. Thanks again for letting us give feedback! If and when I come back to Scottsdale I will return.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-11', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'BgQm6h7Mb1UQgohLyNKdgw', 'review_id': 'c0BR0SegItH9YcnTmC5DXg', 'text': "A MUST!!!!! Ask for SAM!!! I'm serious, he is what made our whole experience! Amazing recommendations, AH-MAZING food and fantastic drinks! My husband got the Manhattan and I had a France white wine ($5 on HH 3-6 M-F) and an espresso martini! TO DIE FOR!!! We also got the hummus & flatbread, cheese & meat (HH $6), Chop Salad (like a boss!!!) and scallops!!!! Ohhhhh and we had this phenomenal peanut butter and chocolate dessert. Most importantly - ask for SAM! He will make sure you LOVE what you get! Never met a waiter more passionate about what he does. Go here!!!!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-11', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'pCEzJ918Ce89yqWSxo1M2w', 'review_id': 'vglPEnK3DrmLgfdITiyUWw', 'text': 'Excellent; been there many times.  Especially like the chopped salad and the buttermilk chicken.  nice bar.  nice buzz.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-13', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Me-4XqwO9Qt1NQ49hDdr1A', 'review_id': 'QexBTvZxcMxMQmuPqNY0UQ', 'text': 'This place was all it promised it would be! \nWe were told the wait would be 45 mins so we left our number and went to wander the city but were pleasantly surprised to receive a text about 20 mins later letting us know our table was ready!\nWe snagged an out side table where we could actually hear each other as the inside has a vicious echo that detracts from the ambiance in our opinion...\nOur server was lovely and let us take our time deciding on each course before going to the next...\nWe enjoyed the Famous Chop Salad, to see what the hype was all about and were not disappointed, although can see why other Yelp reviews comment on the smallness of portions. The crunch of the freeze dried corn was unexpected and the smoked Salmon sealed the deal!\nNext we split the Chia crusted Ahi and the Oso Bucco which were both perfectly executed and left us not a prayer of entering any room for dessert! \nWe would absolutely be regulars here if we lived locally!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-14', 'type': 'review'}
