{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'oUPhooLmWM4vNQF21HppaQ', 'review_id': 'VUYvyH2osanfk8e-t1pTSQ', 'text': 'Lucky us coming to Scottsdale during restaurant week!! We had fabulous service and an outstanding meal. Sam was our excellent server and very knowledgeable and friendly   My husband got the cocktail pairing with the prix fix menu. We started with the chopped salad he got his with the smoked salmon and I got the chopped salad with chicken. They were delicious!! Our entree we had the scallops which were rich and flavourful. I had the meatloaf which was very good. Quite rich tasting. Our desserts were really good. We had the\nApple and bacon bread pudding and the peanut butter strata which was bites of peanut buttery heaven!  It was wonderful!!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-22', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'pnBbtog75YNx5XhVij5HRw', 'review_id': '0mAc4gt6KRnCUKxskNlvzA', 'text': 'We sat at the bar for happy hour food was amazing .... Service exceptional . A must try for your taste buds.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-23', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'OTDuJcFS3lpqFoaT5gwUHA', 'review_id': 'ice3PmYtuDFm6Rnp-5Dj_w', 'text': "3.5 stars.\n\nI expected a lot about this restaurant because of so many great Yelp reveiws.\nI was here 2 days ago for restaurant week and it was not bad.. but not exceptional as I expected.\n\n*Service: really nice. Our server was really helpful and funny.\n\n*Atmosphere: Not bad.. but quite noisy for having proper conversation.\n\n*First Course\n-SOUP OF THE DAY\nI don't know what this soup was, but it was kind of... strange. I don't mean it was bad... but not good either. Little bit salty for me.\n-THE ORIGINAL CHOPPED SALAD\nIt was really really nice as I expected. I can go back to this restaurant just for this chopped salad!\n\n*Second Course\n-PAN SEARED SCALLOPS\nI saw some reviews mentioning this menu is a bit salty so I was worried a bit, but it wasn't. It was great. Smooth and delicious!\n-AMARO MEATLOAF\nNot bad.. That's all. It was just ordinary meatloaf for me.\n\n*Third Course\n-PIG IN THE ORCHARD\nThis breadpudding was okay, but not exceptional.\n-PEANUT BUTTER STRATA BAR\nAgain, okay but not that great. Just sweet peanut butter crunch that you can have anywhere else.\n\nMaybe I had expected too much about this restaurant.\nAnyway, it was worth to try.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-05-26', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'FkVGm88oeEkL9NKhDnmQiA', 'review_id': 'mdl7PisgTo_QE7JwpHFJOw', 'text': "I've been here three times in the past week. Love it! Insane comfort foods. Pork osso bucco, fried chicken , all amazing! Pork belly appetizer is crazy great! The cocktails and service are the best. Ask the bartender to make you their version of your favorite drink and you will not be disappointed. I am telling everyone how great this place is and you will be missing out if you try it at least once. Ha... Try it once and you'll be hooked!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-26', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'tvrxyHOpyZffp9naOg8M0w', 'review_id': 'cPB1-SKhKMKsgmcjvlV6yw', 'text': 'Best service!  Alyshah was an amazing bartender and explained all the dishes in such great detail.  Everyone was so hospitable.  This place has the most amazing drinks and food.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-26', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'f4JAb7SZK7cJlnZ1T9mVRg', 'review_id': '9BXWSX4nomAAXrLaGbmdMw', 'text': "Fancy pants meets working class watering hole.  I've visited this spot a few times via friend recommendation on the food.  \n\nPork belly is amazing, shrimp pasta is surprisingly creamy and flavored with garlic and deliciousness.  Mussels are to die for!  \n\nWhat really got me about CPH is the gathering of every day people just wanting to enjoy a drink.  If you're in the service industry this bar will be a second home for you!  In spite of it's romantic feel, candle lit tables and linen tablecloths; you will feel right at home with the friendliest bartenders in Old Town.  \n\nNot pretentious but could be if it wanted to.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-05-29', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'LrIr2cJC4YMGr6jU1pNWAQ', 'review_id': '8FqrmIBwx2j1O2AbUHf64Q', 'text': "So we went during restaurant week last Friday. And definitely had reservations, previously had tried to go to Citizen in April and it was slammed.  \n\nI loved the multiple course menu idea and to be honest I think they should do it often for certain weekends as nothing beats that. We both had the Chopped Salad, which to be honest...was amazing.  Great idea, and it sports it's own Facebook page. We also shared the drink pairing, the first one which was vodka based made sense but we really weren't that interested in it.  For the second course she had the Buttermilk chicken and I the pan seared scallops.  Both were amazing, the grits were very fine and I hate grits.  The grits were quite tasteful.  The second drink was a citrus and gin cocktail, definitely see how it went with the scallops or the chicken, it was good but no idea how it would couple with the meatloaf.\n\nFor our desert I chose the Peanut Butter Strata Bar and she the Pig In the Orchard, the peanut butter strata bar tasted as though I could ascend to heaven.  The bread pudding was ok, but the maple ice cream that came with it was decadent.  The cocktail was patron cafe based and it completely went with either deserts.  \n\nI would say the skills of the bar tender and the chef were in full display, the only thing that could have made this a five star night would have been our waiter being way more attentive.  He gets a pass as it seemed they needed more wait staff, so given how many patrons he had he did good work.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-05-29', 'type': 'review'}
