{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'wSpMpiJ5jGa672lSo0a0Zg', 'review_id': '9rjU_NeswW-bcSszrvTgBA', 'text': "Very loud atmosphere and can't hear each other talk. Food portions pitiful. I had the trout which they expected you to eat the skin. My friend had the chicken and said it was salty. Two people had the scallops, one person had ossu buco and one had the meatloaf. All were acceptable. We all agreed we won't be back not worth the money.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 2, 'date': '2015-06-06', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'MBhvsi8dJTHuaKn4v98XRw', 'review_id': 'Zm3SsAFt_SNqdjnSTTSDAA', 'text': 'Impressive interior, service, food and reasonable prices for such a delightful experience. The buttermilk chicken dish was really good as was the tuna starter. It gets a bit noisy during peak hours but that is hard to avoid at a well run restaurant. It is a little tricky to find as the entry faces East so you access the front door from Craftsman Ct instead of 5th Ave. But the experience is worth the hunt for the door. What can I say? GPS only gets me so close and then I have to figure the rest out for myself!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-06-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'vVhHSRQMBD3I08cpqBDCWA', 'review_id': 'w19ZA-h8hiQDYLd-T2ISBQ', 'text': "Absolutely love Citizen, not only is the food phenomenal but the service is top tiered! Every time I go I always sit in Sam's section. He's so knowledgeable about the food and wine that it makes the evening A +", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-06-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'QSeGx66qgfpGth1gbxs4YA', 'review_id': '2JODGsmAgPt6Y5Tay7cGqQ', 'text': 'GREAT food and great ambiance\n\nhad the chopped salad and buttermilk chicken.  super yummy.  will be coming back!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-06-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 2, 'useful': 4, 'cool': 3}, 'user_id': 'h-1lrW7Thqvi47a9IvE3zg', 'review_id': 'xEqd00LA5yGDJFrI9G0jWw', 'text': "Everything from the service to the drinks to the food was amazing!\n\nWe had a reservation on a Friday at 7:15. When I fist walked in, I was greeted immediately and Matt (with the pretty blue eyes) escorted us to a nice booth for just the two of us and wished me a happy birthday (we were there to celebrate my birthday). \n\nWe ordered the Bacon Fat Heirloom Popcorn to start. It was freshly popped popcorn with actual bacon pieces on top. Yum. Then we shared the Original Chopped Salad. I crave these things so it was all that I'd dreamed of. My hubby ordered the lam burger for dinner (he said it was really good, but wished he had ordered it well instead of medium well) and I got the Truffled Grilled Cheese Sandwich, which had mashed potato on it (holla!) you could also add chicken or bacon, but I opted for it just the way it was. It was so good!\n\nFor cocktails, my hubby had the Beast (tequila cocktail - strong, but with a kick) and I had the Manhattan (strong, but tasty) and the Julep (strong, but sweeter than the Manhattan). They definitely don't skimp on the alcohol and know how to make a good cocktail. \n\nOur server brought out the dessert menu and suggested the bread pudding or the peanut butter bar. We decided to go with the peanut butter bar (chocolate, peanut butter, strawberry jam, white chocolate ice cream). When it came out with no candle, the hubs asked where it was. The server hadn't been told it was my birthday! Pretty blue-eyed Matt had dropped the ball! (Bad Matt, bad). She felt really bad and brought out a candle, which was really very sweet. We then received a visit from the General Manager, Steve. He also felt really bad because they feel a birthday is special and if one chooses to spend it there, then it is a big deal to them. Because of all that, they comped the dessert (birthday dessert is apparently super tiny) and our popcorn AND gave us a $50 gift card to come back and let them make it up to us! \n\nI think they went above and beyond the realm of good customer service and am looking forward to going back. I can't believe it took me so long to go in the first place!  to you, CPH.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-06-12', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'oWoVwc3P_sOOj001kKGVTQ', 'review_id': 'So9STxUu4vJZQEmZDhDb3g', 'text': 'Love the Citizen Public House!  This restaurant has put together some really amazing food and drink for the old town area.  Its a nice change to the Rave going on east of Scottsdale Rd.  Whatever the drink is with Jameson 12 and tobacco leather bitters is phenomenal!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-06-13', 'type': 'review'}
