{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Z7AUXHdJRI-fj42RPc9DQg', 'review_id': 'HxecL2PWHnfsr8JKDMLsEA', 'text': 'Good was awesome. Had the original chopped salad and it was definitely something to try. Finished off with the apple bacon bread pudding and it exceeded all expectations.\n\nThe portions are a little small, but I was still definitely full by the end of the meal. Will be back to try the other things on the menu and the barrel aged cocktails!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-06-17', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'faVvuyxRutEkKX1hK1GuQA', 'review_id': 'ieZtBYDbQatRZb67moJZlQ', 'text': "I've been meaning to get to the Citizen Public House since I heard about it - been on their mailing list, etc., but just never managed to get there.\n\nFinally, a friend was in town and wanted to grab dinner in old town - he said gastropub, so I told him to meet me at Citizen.\n\nI didn't realize that the Cowboy Ciao chef who originated their fabulous chopped salad was the man behind Citizen Public House - when I found that out, we had to start with that!  In case you haven't had it, please allow me to explain.  The plate arrives with lines of chopped salad items, looking like a bunch of colored stripes.  The stripes include dried corn, Israeli couscous, smoked salmon, asiago, pepitas, tomatoes, arugula and currants.  That is topped with a housemade buttermilk dressing and mixed up.  It's a fabulous mix of flavors and textures - a truly wonderful thing to eat.  If you haven't eaten it before, stop reading this and head to Citizen Public House.  Now.  It's ok, I'll wait.\n\nI decided to try the buttermilk chicken for my main course.  Wow.  I was expecting fried chicken (that's usually what comes after 'buttermilk' in a chicken recipe title), but it was grilled.  It was incredibly flavorful.  Very very good.\n\nWe ordered a couple of desserts for the table:  Pig in the Orchard (apple and bacon bread pudding with maple ice cream and blueberry sauce) and the Peanut Butter Strata Bar (white chocolate ice cream, peanut butter crunch and strawberry jam).  The Pig in the Orchard was spot on - order it.  I was a bit 'meh' on the Peanut Butter Strata Bar.\n\nCool vibe at the restaurant, and right in the heart of Old Town (kitty corner from Cartel Coffee - which, of course, you know already, because you always get your espresso there, right?)", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-06-19', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '0jC7S3oLaODBx9g_nLOPLg', 'review_id': 'qFbb9iIfixpttu8_WGyuWQ', 'text': "Buttermilk roasted chicken is on point! My uncle came to Phoenix for work and I'm new to Scottsdale so I had no idea where to take him but I went here off of a local's recommendation and it did not disappoint! My dad came to visit a few weeks later and I took him as well. I got the scallops that time and they were amazing!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-06-20', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '7KS3KW9TdHiKi4aW53e36g', 'review_id': 'vanLlMWgxP1wzP5IcBwokw', 'text': "Great food, great staff and perfect execution. Beyond that, it's hard to add anything substantive to the already long list of great reviews. I can't wait to go back. You will not be disappointed!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-06-21', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '8_prs6VMGCuD_BzTC7VKog', 'review_id': 'FDXas28gBxjlB5G4lQoUHw', 'text': "My fiancee and I recently had an awesome experience at Citizen Public House. We had gotten engaged right before going out that night and we had chosen their restaurant as our destination for where we would spend our evening celebrating. \n\nThe food was terrific, the service was top notch, and everyone there was very personable. Our server, Sam, was really friendly and incredibly knowledgeable. He magically appeared at the table when we needed him and never lingered too long when we were making small talk. Great guy.\n\nI had the filet and told them I'd like it prepared however they recommend it. It came out somewhere around medium-rare and it was perfect. My brand new fiancee had the scallops and said they were an excellent choice.\n\nThis restaurant also does a great job of maintaining the right atmosphere. It's a very nice place and suitable for formal occasions, but it's still a really laid-back environment. It's a good place to be if you want a great meal without a snooty vibe like what you would find at a high end chain restaurant. \n\nCitizen Public House will definitely be my go-to destination when we are celebrating special occasions. They did an amazing job making us feel special and celebrating our engagement with us. I can't recommend this restaurant enough.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-06-22', 'type': 'review'}
