{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '4p94ToSDtPtS0olEqbClkQ', 'review_id': 'Dyo8M5WYHMzAJ8u_vyEE3g', 'text': "Seriously, this wonderful place really doesn't need another 5 star review but, here goes... first, we ate at the bar and received the best service!. Of course, we shared the Chopped salad,a must have... delish! Then we had seared ahi tuna with purple sticky rice....my absolute favorite. So good:) at this point we were stuffed but had ordered the pork belly pastrami. It was good, but, my least favorite; however, my husband gobbled it up. We really enjoyed every single aspect of our experience, from service to food. So happy we chose citizens!!!!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-07-16', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 3, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': 'uc-XXXtFwHXekN0mcVP-eQ', 'review_id': 'A2IIlasGVv3cE9ViNkBA_w', 'text': "This seems to be a happening place, but we were able to make reservations about an hour before dinner on a Saturday night.\n\nI had a couple of cocktails (the grog and something barrel-aged; forgot the name), both of which were better than I expected.\n\nFor dinner, had a few apps--the fondue, the mac and cheese, and the chia tuna. I don't think you can really go wrong with fondue, so that was fine; the chia tuna was decent and I liked the rice it's plated on. The mac and cheese though--WHY would you put tomatoes in mac and cheese?! You're desecrating the dish! It does NOT work. When I ate around the tomatoes, the mac and cheese was great! I don't get it.\n\nOtherwise, I think the restaurant was worthwhile, and I'm glad we stopped by.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-07-20', 'type': 'review'}
