{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'mXXzvds9nQiQpS0qFaF_tQ', 'review_id': 'FBDMatRtscz0po158XFJjQ', 'text': 'We are visiting Scottsdale from Chicago and found Citizens on yelp. We ate here for dinner on a Thursday night. I love the atmosphere. There is a bar in the middle of the restaurant - a great place to hang out for a drink after work or with friends. They have a great beer selection. \n\nOur server was amazing and super nice and had some fabulous food recommendations. My husband and I ordered the famous chopped salad and added the smoked salmon. Hands down this was THE BEST chopped salad I have ever had. I had the scallops with the corn grits. So delicious! My husband got the short ribs with a coffee rub. They were super tender and came with a yummy cherry bbq sauce.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-07-24', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'RLuIzwb0DSTZbUC_UFD1SQ', 'review_id': 'lwgN6VzKjFDzjiZoAXZQsg', 'text': "Bartender Michael is awesome! Good beer on draft, great food as well!! Love the chopped salad! It's unbelievable! Like the chopped salad at cowboy Caio! Yum! Mac & cheese add sausage!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-07-25', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '09ZFWm0feqpxfH8INjSsng', 'review_id': 'h-PIph4_32iotDODoHMAwQ', 'text': 'Very good food and amazing atmosphere. The Chop salad is yummy!!!  The best time to go is 3-6pm, awesome specials!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-07-26', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 2, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'AGxQrQTQKKQAmD7X2HwWVQ', 'review_id': 'HvE-nuvq9CJtKcyGOv-VbA', 'text': 'Nice bar...but know there are no tvs or music.\nFood: \n*watermelon and beet salad- 5 stars. Light and fresh\n*burrata salad-4 stars. You will def need extra bread\n*mac and cheese- 2 stars. Not very cheesy, Luke warm and odd spicing plopped on top.\n*veggie burger- 3 stars. Veggie burger itself was 5 stars but to only have the option of extremely bland, boring potato chips for the price, leaves you feeling taken advantage of. Not to mention you barely get any of them!\n*drinks- ok bartenders that are friendly.\nTotal bill $130. Definitely not worth that...at best half!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-07-27', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'FO_ou-tLnoDXwGTzkvYq0Q', 'review_id': 'l-lkXEt_IumU3gTvC9sDEw', 'text': "I'm gonna file this one under Summer Is The Low Season In Scottsdale.  Nice decor, but as far from the look of a Public House as The W is from a quaint B&B. Came in for a drink and apps.  The chopped salad was tasty. Weirdly it came with smoked salmon and my wife hates smoked salmon.  We didn't know this when ordering because the description on the menu was just a URL to a Facebook page(!). I guess the salad has its own page that we should have consulted.  I had the mac n cheese which was named after somebody so I figured it had to be good, but it was just regular mac n cheese with salsa on top.  No Bueno.  The kicker was that my wife's Manhattan cocktail arrived within 15 seconds of ordering it!  Sounds good but when we asked how it could be that they whipped up a craft cocktail so speedily the barman told us it was for an earlier customer who didn't want it.  And was warm.  As least he took it off the bill--when asked to.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-07-27', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'EUa_Itb3iJvrMhc_zPb21Q', 'review_id': 'qPhQnoGpNk5jA5C4zpkjMw', 'text': 'The chopped salad is a symphony of textures and favors.  So good it has its own Facebook page!Excellent service and delicious food makes this a good choice.  It might be a little expensive, but you are worth it.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-07-30', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'ZKEDymJie4rFbmnrgsLUeA', 'review_id': 'gxDfHbRliuAHds3hAIi_Ew', 'text': 'We were a group of 9 girls on a bachelorette party that stumbled upon this restaurant after checking out a few dives.  We arrived an hour before the scheduled closing time and the hostess was able to find us a table.  To my surprise,  we were seated in a semi private area, almost like a chef\'s table! They call it the "Family Room" ,I felt so special and VIP!\n\nWe ordered a round of specialty cocktails and we each tried a sip of one another. They were all very good.  Not your typical mai tai or sex on the beach drinks but one that required some skills.\n\nSince it was late and we\'ve already had dinner, we ordered some bar snacks and starters.  The waitstaff was extremely patient with us in explaining the drinks and menu, taking pictures of our group and efficient with our orders and requests.  Kudos to the team!\n\nAll the snacks were delicious ! My favorite was the burrata and the bacon fat heirloom popcorn.\n\nif I lived in Scottsdale, I\'d visit again. Until next time...', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-07-31', 'type': 'review'}
