{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'BXP4FRDjPbnwtSc_VpUj4g', 'review_id': 'tZcwXgNdg8gpvsxEw026EA', 'text': "This place is awesome.\n\nI'm new to Scottsdale so I am making a point to go out, check new places out and explore my new home.\n\nI went to this place for dinner and they were amazing.\n\nThe chicken I ordered was probably the best tasting chicken breast I've ever had. The ambience and bar are really cool -- it's trendy but relaxed at the same time and not overly done. Just the right amount of everything. And the service...is next level. I swear the water chick was a machine -- 2 sips and she'd be pouring more.\n\nThat's attention to detail.\n\nThis is going to be my go to spot when people visit, a hot date or just want to hang in Old Town.\n\nBOOM!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-08-06', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 3, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'nMHu8rkh1wkKn5Md0MzNHA', 'review_id': '5eRs0dL50eH17-mioEnwhQ', 'text': "Another visit, this time solo after work. I arrived at 5 on a Thursday eve and it was nearly empty. Scottsdale is a late-night town, so no worries here. \n\nI was given water and menus right away. The hostess announced that it was happy hour, so I was 'coerced' into a beer. \n\nSam approached me shortly later and offered to explain the menu. I wasn't very hungry so I ordered the Chopped Salad and the Chia Seed Seared Ahi Tuna. \n\nMy salad arrived in 5 minutes. The salad I've had numerous times and there are dozens of reviews about it so I'll focus on the Ahi. \n\nIt arrived shortly after my salad bowl was cleared. It was presented with micro greens, fried leeks and an asparagus gastric. The Ahi was seated nicely and was a good portion. Pretty good but not great. I was pining for the fondues that surrounded me. \n\nSam was genuinely happy to greet all his guests and made me feel like an important part of the clientele. Very good customer skills.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-08-06', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '9jU_1wSHnBcChh63tx-22g', 'review_id': 'XW4XONx-VPyusd186GwrHQ', 'text': 'This was our first visit to Citizen Public house. Everything we had was superb. The quality of the food was amazing. The service is top notch, everyone walked with a fast pace and were very Pleasent. We have found our new favorite place in Scottsdale.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-08-08', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'PND1GD46KWwR8pCbjVJtZQ', 'review_id': 'oQg4lf-P2lCt2Y4m_KEI8A', 'text': 'Great drinks and some standouts on the menu. I like the Pubic house salad. This place also wins at ambiance. Not a lot of places lay it out well enough to be social with your group. This one does.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-08-08', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 2, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'l1AqgSvf-yfv2vEkKpSdkg', 'review_id': 'EHDQAlL5rCRT1PXH7i7A5A', 'text': "I would definitely recommend Citizen Public House.  We arrived with no reservation but the team quickly found a spot for us.\n\nGreat gastropub, good prices! Nice ambiance!!  Unique offerings!! The menu was super interesting. I had the fair trade short rib . . . Amazing if you like short ribs! Seasoned well, fell off the bone . . . Yes cooked to perfection. For dessert I had the bag O' bacon brittle . . . Did you see the word bacon?  I think that says it all!!! Yep yummy!\n\nI generally go to this restaurant when I am traveling for work and I recommend it to colleagues and friends when in the Scottsdale area. The service was good, server knew the menu and was extremely attentive, had a good sense of humor.\n\nOne more thing . . . If you like sangria order one . . . I would double down that you will order another one. Enjoy!!!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-08-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '9R-WVyo_f1HKw_l9NjWkCg', 'review_id': '2kBv_0suzPxJjB2u0KV_Vw', 'text': 'The Lamp Pizzeria-the best secret in North Scottsdale.  Excellent salads (healthy) pizza, zucchini cakes and eggplant parmesan on earth.  Great service and a very good Sangria also.  Ask which one is better that day-the bartender, James, will tell you.  Both are usually good....:)', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-08-10', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'Mg_M8_IqC5qTD2XOGtcEnQ', 'review_id': 'C1pr2c3GdfPwTjRVvrrabg', 'text': 'My husband and I love dinning at Citizen Public House.  Great ambiance, food is delicious and the staff is awesome!  Every time we have been here no matter how busy it is, the service is fantastic.  The staff always explains the menu and really takes the time to make sure you feel good about your choice.  We love coming here for dinner because it is guaranteed to be a great experience.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-08-10', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '-A83HA72bXlufufRxghtfw', 'review_id': 'HTJgDcatXTRoOIAcLD-X7w', 'text': "looking back, I think my expectations were a lot higher than the price and thought I was going to find a real gem. \n\nThe service was definitely good, but it was also very rushed. I sat at the bar and ordered the grilled peach salad and the hangar steak. \n\nThe peaches were tasteless and rock hard (although perfect grill marks) and although it was not over dressed, the vinegar just took over because there just wasn't enough flavors on the plate. Even the bacaon lardon crips were 'eh' and I love pork. \n\nThe hangar steak was so-so. But maybe this is my fault. Hangar steak is a great cut of meat if done right and personally, i think the only way to do Hangar is sous-vide that thing for a long slow bath. Otherwise, you don't break down the tough pars and the center is under cooked. \n\nThey slapped some asparagus on top, heaped a bunch of chipolini onions on the side and went light on the sauce. \n\nThere is good potential here and I probably ordered way wrong. I'll give it another try next time i'm in town but I was not overly impressed based on the many stellar reviews.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-08-11', 'type': 'review'}
