{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'WH3Cq5xX5U-PbI1IeqBNZw', 'review_id': 'zT2n1MbGMDxAFPT5--wsUA', 'text': "Excellent. I had the venison and of course the Chopped Salad. Service was great and the food was amazing. One of my new favorites. Can't wait til next time.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-08-13', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'i_tV6D8Y5tzrkGpfX-Pd_w', 'review_id': 'cfPN2Gc5tbq8G8QCAbuGwA', 'text': "First, the chopped salad is probably one of the best salads ever. A must have if you are here. I love that it was mixed table side and my favorite component was strangely the freeze dried corn, very creative! All ingredients went together perfectly. I am not normally a smoked salmon fan either but it all just worked. Our server was friendly and knowledgeable not only about the menu but also wine. Entrees left a bit to be desired...I got the seabass, it was 2 thin filets with skin on. I have always had my seabass as a thick filet and this preparation just didn't do it for me. We did get a bag of their pecan bacon brittle to go and it is delicious, not overly sweet and a bit smokey from the bacon which was nice. The brittle is a great gift and a nice local item. If I lived in Scottsdale I would swing by for a lunch of chopped salad but didn't have strong feelings about return for dinner entrees.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-08-15', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'wj9wbBQPOQ9RG44d1XEl1A', 'review_id': 'ziUuEQxksE1LebA7jnPsyg', 'text': "Great ambiance but a little loud. I couldn't hear what the people were saying just a person over to my left.. Conversation was hard.  The wait staff was friendly and the place was clean.  Very busy place in old town Scottsdale right in the middle of everything and not far from all the bars.  The original chopped salad was amazing!! I've never had anything like it! I would go back again just for the salad!  The short ribs were good and you can fork it off without a knife but I felt like it was a bit dry.  Flavored were good though.  The mash potato was sweet underneath.. Which I wasn't a fan of but I suppose it goes well with the short rib flavor and the coffee compote sauce.  The mint chocolate budino was a little too sweet for me and the mint taste wasn't apparently strong.  The cookie on top was frozen and really hard to break into to share.  The desserts here were not my favorite but a big win with that chopped salad.  The smoked salmon and pesto dressing made the flavors but the kale, sunflower seeds and some black fruit gave it a crunch!  I want it again already!\n\nI liked the salad so much I went back the next day before my flight to get the chopped salad to go so I can eat it for dinner on my way home!!! Loved it and couldn't stop thinking about it!!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-08-16', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': 'hmvM_QOlxN0P9RSqAzlFgw', 'review_id': 'BrFKOQy2BBgW257Ez_ivNQ', 'text': 'Let me start my saying that we had fantastic service at Citizen Public House.   I was not impressed with the atmosphere. The famous Chopped Salad was probably one of, if not the best salads I have ever had.  My friend had the Seabass and it was not a thick filet like we are accustomed to, instead it was two very thin dry pieces with a strange tasting sauce.  I had the short ribs which were flavorful, but inconsistently cooked and the parsnip puree and greens again had a strange taste. At the price point, I would have expected more.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-08-16', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'sFb3nKXNUsSwVOU5qN1cQA', 'review_id': 'IzovlOK4ZZ9y8V2rJ6ZAyw', 'text': 'Not as easy to find as you might hope ... the front door is actually around the corner south of 5th Ave ... but well worth the confusion. Watermelon and cucumber salad was cool, refreshing, and an interesting presentation. Their barrel-aged cocktails will knock your socks off - almost literally - heavy on the alcohol, which I consider a plus in my drinks. Loved the coffee-rubbed short ribs. The accompanying cherry BBQ sauce was the perfect blend of sweet/tart, and wasn\'t thick or gummy as so many BBQ sauces can be. My only complaint about the short ribs was a personal preference issue on the side ... I HATED the pureed parsnips. Think of nasty mashed turnips, and then make them sweet .... BLECH!!! Thank heavens they didn\'t contaminate the ribs (lol). The waitress kindly brought me some mashed potatoes instead. Friends had the Cuban sandwich (pronounced both "tasty" and "huge"), and the chicken ("spicy and delish").  Friendly smiling staff, attentive but not hovering service, altogether a great experience. Word to the wise for anyone with hearing aids or other hearing issues - concrete floors mean the place is super loud.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-08-17', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'lwvg7LhCLwRi4uKjnxOsnA', 'review_id': 'WqqQsFE14_51Dm2GvYFuyA', 'text': "The Chop Salad alone is enough for me to rate this place so highly.  It's what they're most known for.  Get it.  Enjoy it.  You're welcome (psh like i can take credit for suggesting what so many other people have already suggested).  \n\nThe bacon heirloom popcorn is genius.  Instead of butter you use bacon pieces and bacon grease to flavor the popcorn?!  *deep fat kid labored breathing*", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-08-18', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Em37ENOXv7iQ-ePqdg9S4A', 'review_id': '3anPTajuC8PsJDQV8uCfHg', 'text': "The chopped salad was TO DIE FOR, but I wasn't the hugest fan of the short rib entree I got. Overall would recommend this place in Old Town Scottsdale!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-08-19', 'type': 'review'}
