{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 's6Qv_NirggiLjl0hz_lA0g', 'review_id': '0abMsdo8WVJEwEzP70mr_A', 'text': u"My friend and I recently came to Citizen Public House for dinner (Tuesday evening). The restaurant was crowded (past 6pm), but the host was kind enough to offer us a table, as long as we could leave before 8pm as they had reservations. I appreciated that they accommodated us despite their busy schedule. \n\nThe restaurant has a great ambiance and a bar in the center of the place. It was slightly loud but not an annoying level of noise. We went for two beers from the draft beer menu (a house brew and a locaL IPA). We shared a salad as a starter. \n\nOur main courses were really outstanding. My friend had the seared scallops, and I had the amaro meatloaf. I didn't try the scallops myself, but the meatloaf was exquisite. The look if the dish is extremely appealing, to the extent that my friend HAD to try it (picture in the review). It's a delicious veal demi-glac\xe9 meatloaf that comes with roaster zucchini and smashed gold potatoes, and a tasty and rich mushroom cream. It was surprising that this was the cheapest priced item in the menu, at 20 dollars!\n\nIt was my third time in Citizen Public House, and it was consistently outstanding. I've been to this place in both, high season (winter/spring), and low season (summer), and it's always busy, so I really recommend making a reservation.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-09-03', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '5AuQPQeb8-DxAHgit3PUVA', 'review_id': 'nlDVSUU0JzlP1ViTfbx1Uw', 'text': 'Here is a straight up review. Food was decent, prices were avg for Scottsdale, Service was ok as well. Atmosphere is where it lacked. The place echoed and WAY too loud. Almost to the point of annoyance. Unfortunately that is something that would be hard to correct. I still give it 3 stars though', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-09-03', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'uFppZrbeNm7jHjbToYzsBg', 'review_id': 'Bjy50xbFdAAnOg_jLSHuAw', 'text': 'Food was very good. I found the menu to be very small - definitely not enough options. Good service. Very cool neighborhood. We would definitely go back again... Maybe during a different season to see if the menu changes as well.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-09-05', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'H2QwZDnYFbGFHcnhzIwMmg', 'review_id': 'Z9x6sOw6D1YFMFwiDHqhfA', 'text': 'Came here for my birthday dinner and was very happy with my choice. Citizen Public House has a deceiving facade, but upon entrance you are greeted with the cozy atmosphere. Tables are lit by single votive candles completing the mood. The drink menu is filled with craft brews, hand crafted cocktails and a diverse wine list. We shared the famous Chopped Salad and were not disappointed, very rich and refreshing! We had the chicken fried duck leg, the Cubano, and the pork belly pastrami. The Cubano was fantastic my favorite! We will definitely be back again!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-09-08', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '32ZiXU5dRb4ve2d3QpsWVw', 'review_id': 'vvweb9D6gLC361owHi6rDA', 'text': "Great service. Sat at the bar, and the bartender Eli was immediately available to assist. Granted it was a slow night, so that's probably why I got immediate service. While I'm regretting not getting the short ribs, I was still reasonably happy with the venison that I received. However, I was left a little disappointed, because it was missing something. Additional searing, some salt and peppering, etc. It just wasn't up to snuff. It was tender as can be, however if I'm paying $38 for two medallions of meat, I expect to be blown away. I was less than blown away, since it just tasted like... well... meat. No complexity of flavor or aroma. It could appeal to people, but not me. This rating is more for the service and ambiance than for the food. Hope they improve this dish.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-09-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '8EoHxWPqYqx-I8Uom7sOcQ', 'review_id': 'hxGX0XeUDxQWTwpT5KkM2w', 'text': 'This is an awesome restaurant right in the heart of old town. I will start by saying the service was disappointing probably around 2 stars but the quality and creativity of the food and beverage is awesome and changed the experience. Server was rushing us through the meal, and my girlfriend had to push her for a description of the menu. She had a giggle that made us both a little uncomfortable. With all this said we heard other wait staff and they seemed awesome so I believe this is a one off. I had an amazing meat loaf dish and the chicken fried duck leg is amazing as well. Great spot to check out for date night', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-09-11', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'abO0-xrd2HCI0NMlleMZGg', 'review_id': 'GIsZAfMkHJrgPPKgSsWySA', 'text': 'My husband and I been here several times for dinner and drinks. The food is excellent, different, fresh, and oh so flavorful.Thats what keeps us coming back. We had one oops experience sitting at the bar on our very first visit to Scottsdale. We selected to try this shot of Tequila because the bottle it came in was pretty cool looking. Come to find out that shot was $25 a piece, but that was more on us and if we had known we would have savored the taste instead of downing it.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-09-12', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Im0DRhy0U7ZjRQBnvZEidQ', 'review_id': '4Ey3SBIONEdVoew_l2wtqw', 'text': "The Good: \nThe Duck and steamed buns appetizer\nThe cocktails ( second generation was smooth, light refreshing for the AZ heat)\n\nThe Average:\nThe scallops which is supposedly their top dish, was average at best. \nThe Meatloaf was dry and taste more like a Salisbury steak. \n\nThe bad: \nService was the worst. The appetizers came out quick, then the waitress forgot about our drinks, entrees for a good 40 mins. She finally came around and realized that we were not being served and finally got our meal which was room temperature (because she didn't pick up when it was ready). She was serving a larger party as well, and was tending to that table the majority of the night while neglecting us. \n\nNot sure what all the hype is about, but you can easily get a better meal elsewhere along with better service.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 2, 'date': '2015-09-13', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'suRGJir2NmSZVnixdIN22Q', 'review_id': '5qFurs4S5l0i0dCwG4TZ8A', 'text': "I would rank the Original Chopped Salad as one of the best salads I've had. Although I don't like ordering salad at restaurants (meat for me!), I would order this in a heart beat. I don't even like salmon, and I loved this!\nI also got the Pork Belly Pastrami and also enjoyed this as well. I loved the brussel sprout sauerkrout on top, and the pork belly just melted in your mouth. Pork belly can come across as overly fatty, but this was so tender, and the flavor was incredible. \nBoth of these dishes amazed me- so I ordered another: the Ramen with pork belly in Chinese 5-spice, shiso leaves, bean sprouts, and soft marinated egg in a pork-based stock. I didn't think the ramen was on par as the chopped salad and the pastrami, but clearly, I'm Asian. I thought the ramen more had Chinese flavor than the traditional flavor, and it felt more like a bowl of Chinese noodle soup. However, the broth was pretty tasty, and the pork belly and egg were done well. Noodles were fresh.\n\n...I am so sad that I live so far from here...", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-09-18', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '8Dp6XSahPzozugRlGyqK4w', 'review_id': 'p_BGV9HwY1ItfFNRgSKWAQ', 'text': "Always wanted to try this place and went  for my birthday was not at all disappointed let's start with the service Sam was our waiter and this guy was the poster child for exuberance at a restaurant who knew was our first time he gave his selections  we chose one he just called the salad it's a deconstructed jem that just explode in your mouth prepared the table and it's absolutely outstanding I went with the pork belly pastrami I know it sounds odd but absolutely fantastic we did start with an appetizer we chose the fondue will say probably a little too many pieces of bread out of for a little more sausage and the Pears was just a perfect match for this beer fondue the desert that was a caramel chocolate extravaganza was definitely enough for two and pack we can't even finish it was so rich but it was certainly outstanding drinks were great amdd service was top notch really can't seem to say much more about it except had a great time definitely will be back", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-09-18', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'l1ig37X_kUrqolYFFxB6Yw', 'review_id': '9XswO0EckGq3SLQr5uNPsw', 'text': 'Amazing!!!! Citizens has a great atmosphere, great service & incredible food!!! Id eat there every day of the week if I could!!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-09-19', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 3, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '68zB7FYPFA8xy0UfHJGuPw', 'review_id': 'vxXwzHswF5q6zrF_HmWevA', 'text': "Tried CPH during Restaurant Week. My husband and I tried the salad that was a mixture of roasted corn, couscous, smoked salmon and various other ingredients all made for a unique and delicious offering. We both had the scallops which were perfectly cooked.and very tasty. The dessert was a blueberry bread pudding which was okay but not remarkable. We went with the cocktail pairings all were very unusual and a little odd. Nothing we would order again. The service was good. The bad was we were severed quickly and were out in under an hour and the atmosphere is far from relaxing, way too noisy. We couldn't hear each other; there is no way you could carry on a conversation in a normal tone of voice. Doubt we'll be back.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-09-22', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '7HludhMS-q6RW5rEhSjC8g', 'review_id': 'eS7bKhr9oxcfZDrEjHDjcA', 'text': "Great vibe. Met a friend for drinks, then for dinner. Great HH drink...limited HH snacks but they make up for it with the entrees . It was my first trip.....but won't be my last. Friendly staff as well.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-09-24', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'yf1gnTwX2xodchX4PX6l8g', 'review_id': 'mHKG1c_kRKxk2WIfwGmHwQ', 'text': 'Great spot to wind down the night. Craft cocktails and unique food menu. The hummus, tzatziki, and fresh grilled pitas were filling and flavorful. Services is quick and the staff makes you feel like family. We were served the house salad ON THE HOUSE!  Thanks Michael..', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-09-27', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 2, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'otwauMc-Jigv-AgAj_S99w', 'review_id': 'Sq-f9t2hZdh7_dGHpKww3g', 'text': "The first thing our waiter suggested was the Original Chop Salad, and quite frankly it was the most surprising and delicious part of the experience! Service was phenomenal, we had a very professional yet personable waiter who knew the menu backwards and front.\n\nOur main course included the the chop salad, coffee rubbed shortribs (cherry bbq sauce), and amaro meatloaf w/potatoes. The rib portions were small but made up for it in taste and quality of cut. Our heart of caramel and mint chocolate budino were perfectly refreshing as finishers- both the mint ice cream and roasted white chocolate ice cream were incredible!  Presentation was all very photo worthy, but we restrained ourselves ;)\n\nAtmosphere is open and lively, moderate lighting and white table cloths, small candles atop- the bar is right in the center of the room. Our party of two went on a Monday night- I'm sure it would be much more crowded on a weekend. It's right in Old Town Scottsdale, after all. I definitely recommend anyone to try this place- I'll be back soon.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-09-29', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'HZSgthVOWzxt9VDyqk18ag', 'review_id': '7BMgQRZ03v3iHIn6CNQnTQ', 'text': "Bradley was RAD! This was our first restaurant and meal in Scottsdale after having just got off a flight and it was such a phenomenal experience. I ordered the short ribs which were coffee rubbed with an amazing cherry sauce. Brad brought us bacon fat popcorn as a surprise and suggested the best menu items. The Original Chopped salad was out of this world, same with the Mac N Cheese!! We had such a lovely evening and he didn't rush our meal at all. It was a very relaxing and enjoyable meal. Thanks Brad!!!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-04', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '97uszv9AN9zlhpI7XMs1_A', 'review_id': 'VqmhLBZKAx9UcXq5mv69pg', 'text': "I don't always get emotional over salad, but when I do, it's exclusively at Citizen Public House.  Had a delightful dinner consisting of two of their now world famous Chop Salad along with fondue.  Sam was our dining consultant...not a server and definitely not a waiter.  Ask for him when you go.  He truly loves what he does and it shows.  This is the only restaurant where I've geeked out about freaking salads, but they're geek-worthy.  Service here is top notch.  The next time my wife and I find ourselves in Scottsdale, we're here.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-05', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'ozZzvVBIL8val9BvJPMkuQ', 'review_id': 'eVraut6rziOpOL1STzUH8w', 'text': "I'm writing this review before I even finish my dinner. This place just does it all well. Came here solo on business, sat at the bar. The Chopped Salad is unbelievable--perfect texture and variety of flavor---and the Meatloaf hits the spot with a great balance of flavor. Beers are great; cocktails look even better.\n\nAnd the SERVICE really sets this place above and beyond. The bartenders check on me and keep my water filled every few minutes. They give me tactful recommendations and explain my beers to me when I ask as if they've worked at a brewery for years. \n\nWhat a great evening experience.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-06', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'xREUqJ6i-j_TpFJd2kP8qw', 'review_id': 'xfpXYBRZYHe-V2NKKXnI9Q', 'text': "Had a fantastic dinner here.  Cocktails were delicious, particularly the barrel-aged ones: I had one similar to an Old Fashioned (can't remember the exact name), and The Import: one of the most unique and manliest cocktails I've ever had, containing Jameson, Tawny Port, Guinness foam, and tobacco bitters.  I would order both again.  The Chopped Salad was the standout appetizer, but the bacon-fat popcorn was addictive.  The hummus was good, but not a standout.  For my entree I had scallops, which were perfectly cooked, and topped with generous bacon lardons.  Service was very attentive, and our server was affable and very knowledgeable about the menu.  I hope to return.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-08', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'vmpK5VVMxsfN-MHzX0AXkQ', 'review_id': '25trixq1Q2hbNRRIBsKR5Q', 'text': "Food was ok. Loved the salad and apps (especially the fondue). Chicken breast was so so - really big breast and I typically don't enjoy those.  Three stars tho is because the noise level in this restaurant is so loud you cannot hear across the table.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 3, 'date': '2015-10-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'fB0u0tHVtT2KMF1B-hRGhw', 'review_id': '_Oj9mR-YZMlhDfww9vyApA', 'text': "Simple menu with tasty selections. You have to try the chop salad! It's the best salad I have ever had. Good atmosphere, great place to take a date because it is romantic. Its also is in the heart of old town Scottsdale which is convenient", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'SoZWIuaqeUg19dkUAE2yEw', 'review_id': 'ETq7eiBGnjMghBzmmc9yHQ', 'text': "Trendy, casual, and warm sets the scene for perhaps one of the most unique and flavorful dining experiences I have had in recent memory. Easily the most well deserved 5 star rating I have given out in 2015.\n\nSave yourself the trouble of looking at the menu! Look to your skilled servers for advice and direction. Our server Sam was the sever that every restaurateur wishes they had. Polite, quick, and devoted to the menu. Sam directed us immediately to The Original Chopped Salad, a recommendation from a local friend sent us to the Bernie's Mac 'N Cheese - neither of which left me underwhelmed or with an empty stomach. To boot we finished off with the Heat of Caramel to drive home a winning experience.\n\nThe Original Chopped Salad: Everything you think you know about salad just died. This salad packs a seductive and savory experience that is nothing like any salad you have ever experienced. Select the smoked salmon and each bite will erupt in your mouth with sweet, tart, and smokey delectably unique taste. Deconstructed and prepared at your table this event is a must.\n\nBernie's Mac 'N Cheese: This is the type of Mac 'N Cheese your Mom would have made if she didn't suck at making Mac. Slathered in rich gorgonzola cheese topped with heaps of sweet grilled tomatoes, this is not like anything you have spooned into you gullet in the past year. \n\nIn short, you must go here be call yourself a truly enlightened foodie. Oh and by the way, dinner for two for a mere $40 including tip - I walked away stuffed, pleased, and eager for more. Bravo!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-11', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 2, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '8jNY8udHPpBHrZwuqb7q1w', 'review_id': 'W-wWzPj3l7DxNV0w563Bjg', 'text': "Tonight was my one year anniversary with my girlfriend. We wanted a safe bet for good food, we are big fans of the Gladly, and were willing to pay a larger bill. Sadly we only achieved the later. I am hoping this was an off night as all the other reviews were rather strong.\n\nFirst we were presented with the Summer menu, which being October should have been the Fall menu.\n\nWe had the tuna and peaches on the appetizer list. The tuna was really good 8/10 - slight fishy taste, but hey its Arizona. The sea is far away. The baked peach salad was pretty bad though. The lettuce and bacon was ok, but the peaches were hard as rocks. Its a dish we have all done and if you have peaches a little less than ripe you can usually wing it, but these were solid like a rock. They were most likely very apt for the Summer menu, but as it is Fall, peaches are no longer in season.\n\nWe ordered the scallops as our main. I'm a big scalop guy, but these were undercooked and leveled off with a huge pile of greens on top. The photograph of the scallops on yelp showed them with a deep brown sear. Ours were white with a hint of brown and pink in the middle. \n\nI think the best part of the meal was true to scottsdale form, the cocktail. Extra strong which made my girlfriend a little more flirty. \n\nWe decided to cut our losses and go to a different restaurant. Frank and Alberts over at the Biltmore. If you want a really good dinner and ambiance you should check this spot out.\n\nThe meal came to $80, and we were charged an extra $8 for an extra scalop on the plate which we left behind as a casualty of a bad dining experience.\n\nMoral of the story: if you are into the scottsdale drinking scene bring your date here they serve a strong cocktail, if you are into good food look elsewhere.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 1, 'date': '2015-10-11', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'DoWoU8jfwCh9DyjEECTyGg', 'review_id': 'DxqAw72gK-xBLbKSKaYosw', 'text': "This place is great! The atmosphere is modern and chic and the prices are reasonable given the high quality food. My husband and I shared the chopped salad, mac & cheese, and heart of caramel. We were stuffed by the end and spent less than $20 per person! What a deal!\n\nI have never had a salad as original as the chopped salad at Citizen Public House. The presentation is beautiful and the salad is tossed table side. I honestly can't describe it, you will just have to try it yourself!\n\nThe mac and cheese was made with Gorgonzola cheese and topped with a tomato chili relish. It is decadent with a hint of spice. Very filling!\n\nThe heart of caramel should be called death by chocolate. It has a great smooth texture and is served with salted caramel and white chocolate ice cream. What a great finish to the meal!\n\nHad to go back a second time. Got the chopped salad, meat loaf, and butter cake. The meat loaf was good, but not great. The butter cake was really good, but a little small for the price. Still love this place!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-12', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'R_JF6xNr1PdkwWm8qryOAg', 'review_id': 'SCraJJEOJ1B7G3ppwdKNxQ', 'text': "Citizen Public has some great reviews and they are justified.   My husband and I were seated in the smaller dining area inside.    It was  a nice  location out of the heat on the patio, and quieter than the big dining area.     \n\nWe got there at the end of the Happy Hour and tried the Artichoke (soooo tender), and the Bone Marrow with Ricotta Pancakes (pancakes were great rolled around the marrow but there was very little marrow to share). \n\nThe Grilled Peach Salad sounded very good and it was different so we both ordered that.    We were disappointed and we provided feedback to our waiter.  The peaches were not ripe.  They were too hard and lacked flavor.   (More on this below).\n\nFor our main courses my husband had the Pan Seared Scallops (which he loved) and I had the Flat Iron Steak (very good!)   Partway through our meal our waiter showed up with  the chicken version of their famous chopped salad to make up for the disappointing peach salads.    I had told him earlier I wasn't fond of smoked salmon so he had one made with chicken instead.       OMG!  I could not stop eating it.   It was delicious and full of different tastes and textures.  \n\nWe topped off the meal with the Heart of Caramel dessert.  We were already stuffed but couldn't pass up trying a dessert (good!).  We will be back.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-12', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'DvNtfrbk_kl4JDM-9kGBrA', 'review_id': 'UqhMEuxyIK2diT8KChugDw', 'text': 'Went in for drinks.  Nice place. Outdoor patio. Order the Beast Cocktail. We a nice strong pour. Did not order any food.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-10-13', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'it9o1JPGqbfFizf1pgmkDg', 'review_id': 'eVM_n8UkYLpNFOrBdk-o9w', 'text': "Citizens public house is an excellent place for a cocktail. We had great service and really enjoyed our craft cocktails. They are the real deal and boozy but well crafted and perfectly balanced. The night we were here they had the patio open which allowed a fresh breeze into the restaurant. There as a good steady crowd and the food looked amazing. The menu has small plates and offers a variety of options with some unique choices. The drink menu is also very unique. The cocktail my husband had was made with port wine, guiness foam, and bourbon. It was actually tasty and he really enjoyed it. I had a Manhattan and enjoyed it as well. This appears to be a great place for a date or special event or if you're just looking to have an excellent dining experience. We will be back when we're back in the Pheonix area!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-15', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 2, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'QqXKGqTAh5jQsmkFPpsmzw', 'review_id': 'RGpuuM8xOjEhHUxRbma9wg', 'text': "While traveling to Scottsdale for a conference at the JW Marriott, we decided to venture off the resort to have dinner in Old Town Scottsdale.  Citizen Public House came highly recommended, and delivered a tremendously fun dining experience last night.\n\nOn a Wednesday night, Citizen was still pretty busy when we walked in around 8:30.  We were taken care of my Greg, who was one of most enthusiastic servers I've ever encountered, but he was a true service professional who really knew the menu from top to bottom, and talked about the cocktails, food, and dessert options with no difficulty, giving his appraisals as he went.\n\nWe started with the Char Siu pork tacos and Citizen's well-known chopped salad, which was mixed tableside by Greg.  I can see why people love the chopped salad, particularly with respect to its presentation, but the Char Siu tacos, while good, were less memorable.\n\nFor entrees we tried the evening special, a Bavette steak, the short ribs, and the venison loin.  The highlight for me was the venison loin, which was presented rare, exactly as ordered.  Nice cold center but well seared on the outside.  The bavette steaks were not quite as successful.  Based on preferences at the table, one was ordered super rare (blue) the other was ordered medium rare.  However, both came out pretty similarly cooked (I'd call it rare), and in fact the one ordered medium rare seemed to be the one less cooked despite the fact that it came out a few minutes later.   We enjoyed the steaks nonetheless.  Finally, the braised short rib was well executed with a coffee rub, again not particularly memorable but still a dish we enjoyed.\n\nI really enjoyed the cocktails and in particular their barrel aged options.  The Instant Gratification was a scotch-based cocktail with Cognac and Amaro, and it's pure alcohol.  Definitely a slow sipping cocktail.  I also enjoyed tasting the Manhattan, which was well-made.  Their wine list is reasonably extensive and has options in all price ranges. We enjoyed the 2013 Chappelet Mountain Cuvee for $45.\n\nOverall, this was a tremendously fun restaurant that was enhanced by our excellent server, Greg.  While the execution on the food was a bit uneven, I'd give high marks for presentation, quality of cocktails, and ambiance.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-10-15', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 2, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'mbJCCaGu3BU9MuGUiG0pRA', 'review_id': '6Slh4H-stsjavirFPDtIBA', 'text': "The original chopped salad is as good as people have made it out to be! It was simply fantastic especially with the presentation and all the ingredients of the salad blended very well together. I can definitely see why this is their most popular dish. The pork belly pastrami was very good as well and probably my second favorite after the chopped salad. Lastly, the chicken fried duck leg was not bad but compared to the other options I thought it was just OK.\n\nI missed out on the happy hour unfortunately and didn't get any drinks on my first visit, however seeing as how I enjoyed the appetizers here I plan on making a return visit here to try out their drinks and of course to get the chopped salad again.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-17', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 3}, 'user_id': 'SoZWIuaqeUg19dkUAE2yEw', 'review_id': '--aNmADym5CBFXQgo5UEJg', 'text': "Trendy, casual, and warm sets the scene for perhaps one of the most unique and flavorful dining experiences I have had in recent memory. Easily the most well deserved 5 star rating I have given out in 2015.\n\nSave yourself the trouble of looking at the menu! Look to your skilled servers for advice and direction. Our server Sam was the sever that every restaurateur wishes they had. Polite, quick, and devoted to the menu. Sam directed us immediately to The Original Chopped Salad, a recommendation from a local friend sent us to the Bernie's Mac 'N Cheese - neither of which left me underwhelmed or with an empty stomach. To boot we finished off with the Heat of Caramel to drive home a winning experience.\n\nThe Original Chopped Salad: Everything you think you know about salad just died. This salad packs a seductive and savory experience that is nothing like any salad you have ever experienced. Select the smoked salmon and each bite will erupt in your mouth with sweet, tart, and smokey delectably unique taste. Deconstructed and prepared at your table this event is a must.\n\nBernie's Mac 'N Cheese: This is the type of Mac 'N Cheese your Mom would have made if she didn't suck at making Mac. Slathered in rich gorgonzola cheese topped with heaps of sweet grilled tomatoes, this is not like anything you have spooned into you gullet in the past year. \n\nIn short, you must go here be call yourself a truly enlightened foodie. Oh and by the way, dinner for two for a mere $40 including tip - I walked away stuffed, pleased, and eager for more. Bravo!\n\nBack for a second night - I walk away pleased again! Encore!!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-17', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'xfCekGC_XoFBjSkSWpcA2w', 'review_id': 'uHVXM-HnFCPh3OqBcJm2Aw', 'text': 'Excellent in all ways. Scallops are fabulous and drinks are always unusual.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-10-18', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 3, 'useful': 5, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': 'NRgjvzgqPfhQaQRpw_t9Ew', 'review_id': 'rqberLT0IWWlUzSjPt5oPA', 'text': "Pros:\n1. The scallops, meatloaf, and sea bass entrees were all very delicious and flavorful and cooked properly. The meatloaf is very filling; it comes with mashed potatoes that is so velvety and buttery. I loved the sauce that came with the scallops. \n2. Convenient location; lots of parking (free)\n3. Food arrives quickly\n\nCons:\n1. The restaurant is very dimly lit.\n2. Extremely loud, not from the music but from so many people packed into one room\n3. The actual restaurant doesn't look as nice as in the pictures. The place is kind of plain. \n\nDefinitely a place to go to for the food more than the ambience, and I would go during an off peak time so that you can hear what your dinner mates are saying.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-10-18', 'type': 'review'}
