{'votes': {'funny': 3, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'TCPz2W_1iO93SYOfrVShBg', 'review_id': 'I3nP9q-99SkSV71pB1DJ_A', 'text': 'We went a year ago and loved it. This time it was awful. Short ribs were dry and full of gristle. The greens were tough and bitter. The scallops were gritty. The noise level was so loud we couldn\'t talk to each other without saying "what?"  A really bad experience. I wouldn\'t go back.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 2, 'date': '2015-11-04', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': 'rOuKN7Kf6P9LbXJqD5yAjw', 'review_id': 'FMNwVtxJho4SLB67_t-iCQ', 'text': "I had a first date at CPH 2 months ago and had an amazing time. Great food and drinks as well as an attentive and professional staff and fun atmosphere. \n\nLast night was our 2 month anniversary (insert your sarcasm here) and chose to revisit CPH. I made an online reservation and stated in the notes the info about our anniversary and if they could do something special. Who knew they actually read those things. \n\nAlthough we had a reservation we had to wait 15 for a table to open up. The place was packed. No biggie. We saddled up to the bar for some drinks. My girlfriend wanted to start drinking bourbon. I asked if they had an obscure brand that was a mellow starting point as far as bourbons go and they did. Every 5 minutes a different host came up to us to let us know our status and that we would be seated shortly. And we were. The manager came over and wished us a happy anniversary. Much appreciated. \n\nWhen we were seated the server brought us a little gift which was amazing and a great surprise. \n\nThe food was amazing and so was our server. The entire staff was friendly, attentive, gracious, funny and welcoming. On the way out I thanked the manager and let him know we'll be back each month to celebrate our first date there. What a great and unexpected experience. More restaurants should take a queue from CPH on how to treat customers. Thanks for making our special night yet another night to remember.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-11-05', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'AZ2U6OQUfsMZFmQtu_Wcug', 'review_id': 'KwMNQIhI1mfWHdX5hAOHOw', 'text': "Awesome place!! Very busy!! Order the chopped salad and you will understand why it has its own Facebook page. Amazing!! \n\nChicken pot pie was good too. It is deconstructed but very good. Too bad there wasn't more. \n\nA must go to place in Scottsdale!!", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-11-06', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '7k2X7Wp8w4kJ1jc6GX4ynQ', 'review_id': 'BVzFCzRcHIOpXqoJxryBeg', 'text': "So I went out in the area and went in and asked if do could do some take out (surprise, surprise) cuz the place didn't look like a take out place....\n\nI ordered the original chopped salad of which the hostess recommended.\nNot sure if I LOVE it.\n\nIt has not only different textures, a favorite of mine in salads, but whole different flavors.\n\nFirst of the house made buttermilk dressing was a bit too garlicky for my personal taste because it over powered the other flavors in the dressing like the pepper, the buttermilk, and maybe something could not taste it.\n\nThe salad was fresh and definitely had different tastes and textures. The dried corn was interesting as it popped and fizzled in your mouth. The Israeli couscous was blank and possibly overlooked. The greens and tomatoes were diced and were fresh. There was an umami  taste in the dish possible from the smoked salmon or it could have been the salad dressing mixing with the dries corn bits. Not really sure. Could not taste much of anything else.\n\nI got bread with the dish which was way too much food for me. And to be honest I could tell what kind of bread it was. Foccicia? For me the bread was an overkill, though I tried  2-3 pieces, and a bit on the dry and plain side.\n\nOverall an interesting combination and one I would need to possibly revisit since I currently am slightly congested.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-11-07', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'YqMy40TlajKqRSz5gE1Mvg', 'review_id': 'nSzgO_99Y0VBvq05zGN5ng', 'text': "The Famous Chopped Salad is to die for! I think I could eat it every day. I ordered the scallops without bacon as my main course. I would have given 5 stars but my scallops came with bacon. The server quickly re plated my entree. The scallops were delicious as well! I had the Cider Shandy and Paloma to drink. They were good but I wasn't overwhelmed. They just changed their cocktail menu so I'm wondering if that had something to do with it.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-11-08', 'type': 'review'}
