{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'hry_sPPnrebkxRn1d0iMKg', 'review_id': 'MlkLsGvg5IcXlbRj36GOSA', 'text': "For anyone that wants a wicked cocktail, a great meal, and an atmosphere that is part speakeasy (barrel aged cocktails by a mixologist with a heart) and part modern incarnation of Cheers (truly felt like everyone that worked there new my wife's and my name)...go to this place.  Everything from the bar is a gift (thanks to Michael who is a true artist and a helluva guy) and anything from the kitchen is worth skipping meals for the rest of the week (this ain't your mom's meatloaf).  Hands down the best meal in Scottsdale.  So bummed this place isn't just down the street from my house in Portland.  Citizen something special. Go there tomorrow.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-11-15', 'type': 'review'}
