{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': '1308Z0cJ2Mh5sQ9GwMpV6A', 'review_id': 'gR5L32IMlu82tyUR6Dbyqg', 'text': "Multiple visits. Great staff.  Great menu. Fair prices for quality. Chopped salad is a must. Can't wait to return.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-11-26', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'Vkfa-wnWTl95kz3YWRtEgw', 'review_id': 'Ea6gpmEh9afhjpNWkMJNBA', 'text': "This place is amazing. I was in Scottsdale for a concert and we decided to come here because of the yelp hype and I couldn't believe how good the chopped salad was. I asked them to put the smoked salmon on the side and ate it as much as I wanted with the salad instead of having so much of it in the salad at once. It was the most amazing thing ever. We ordered a chopped salad to go when we left haha. I really liked the scallops I got, too. Can't wait to go back to Arizona just for this place.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-11-27', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'LOCBp2C0upFIirHU7k_TUw', 'review_id': '7-TcMof17rLntmEc9QJAxA', 'text': 'This was a magnificent discovery.  \nI deeply appreciate a phenomenal steak house, etc.  But this place, beautifully lit, graciously served, is just an instant favorite.  The creators of this menu are truly magicians -- drawing together unlikely but absolutely ingenious ingredients.  A simple salad with silky salmon, freeze-dried corn, dried blueberries, and greens provides an exploration in which each taste is different, the textures play brilliantly off of each other..... Take this into a smoky pastrami dish with Brussels sprouts, a meatloaf that is simply mysteriously better than any before..... I have eaten many great meals.  \nRarely have I been so delighted by the sensory imagination of a chef.....', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-11-28', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': 'bUKEznD2WlMkkdsUv8oK0w', 'review_id': 'rbBer7HPdLxehuTjrdTabQ', 'text': "Came here last saturday night without a reservation and sat at the bar.  We met the bar manager and he basically guided us through the night with his recommendations for food and drink.  It was a great experience.  Unforgettable.  You've got to eat the scallops!  Highly recommend this place. We found it because the yelp reviews were high and they didn't let us down.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-12-09', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'kh_tpXCTueVTcC7SCIxxKA', 'review_id': 'PlCynnDv3AuSIda8jeEeQA', 'text': '5 stars. Service, food, atmosphere, friendly staff and very knowledgeable waiter. There was no waiting (for table or for food) even on a Friday night. Food was phenomenal. Love pastrami pork belly, their specialty salad and my main dish (spare rib).', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-12-12', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'wBi0I2QcqZtNOh21WlBVKA', 'review_id': 'lX3eZPBGXqAvv9MT9o-6NA', 'text': 'Pricey but good. Excellent Short Ribs and wonderful Rack ofLamb served attentively in a nice ambiance. Gotta go back for the Chef\'s Salad which sounds wonderful. Disappointing array of tap beers for a "public house."', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-12-14', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 2, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '9lo5EtOfzFM0_Y3Jp5Xhqg', 'review_id': 'mXG-FCtUtQeyfXLPuoua_w', 'text': u'Let me start by saying that I had heard some great things about this restaurant. So when I walked in and saw a plain Jane restaurant with a concrete floor and nothing to absorb the noise, I was surprised. It is loud and there is not much ambiance. On a brighter note, our waiter was one of the best. He brought us drinks quickly and gave us good advice. Our table started off with the fondue which was very nice and great for sharing and the tzatziki. For dinner we ordered the scallops, the meatloaf, the short ribs, and rabbit (not my order). Overall it was okay, but not amazing. Apparently the rabbit was the best meal on the table. My short ribs were a little dry but the parsnip pur\xe9e that accompanied it was delicious. We had the dude jar for dessert which won me over. I would give the food and ambiance three stars but because of the waiter I bumped it to four stars.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-12-15', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 1, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'LOCBp2C0upFIirHU7k_TUw', 'review_id': 'ES0jtS5OvjWFAIT6nkNNtQ', 'text': "WOW!!!!\nOne of the most creative and delicious dining experiences in years!  \nMy wife and I were traveling, and had had a kind of meh day.....I read some of the reviews for this place -- and was intrigued by the menu.\nWhat a creative master chef.....Everything was delicious -- fabulous!  It was the kind of place that made me very sorry to have just the one night in town, because I would have loved the opportunity to come back again and again -- the menu was full of irresistible things that I just couldn't sample.  If you're in Scottsdale for the night or live there full-time but haven't yet tried this place -- go!  It's really one of the most creatively designed eating experiences I've ever had.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-12-16', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'M3H8du5TxqlTY7qJd4FDbw', 'review_id': '8sbBZkUUnIz6cPyv0651-w', 'text': 'I used to go to Citizen Public House\'s bar and order the Sangria and go there just for the Sangria. I bet I funded the Sangria bank all on my own. When my husband and I went out last night,I was super disappointed to see they got rid of it so I ordered the Highlands Drifter\nand I was not disappointed. Not as awesome as the Sangria but it was tasty. \nOur dinner and service was fantastic. I ordered the Chop Salad with smoked salmon which is consistently good and the Cauliflower Salad, as an appetizer. The Cauliflower Salad was a little bland in some (few) parts but overall very good. My husband said his "meat was perfect". One knock is their menu is a bit small, but man, they do NOT disappoint in their meat and veggies! So vegetarians and carnivores and pescatorians can all love each other and get along at Citizen!\nI love to end on a sweet note, you cannot go wrong with their Heart of Caramel dessert. If you\'re looking to trash your New Year\'s resolution to eat fewer sweets, do it. New Year\'s resolutions are an exercise in futility anyway.Wowza! My mouth is watering just yelping!\nOne final point, our service has consistently been awesome. Our waiter was quick and when the kitchen was backed up due to a party of 30, he let us know they were running a little behind. \nFour stars because they ditched my favorite drink but I will be back!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-12-19', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'user_id': 'FykVufQvDKBXzvFyJrxodA', 'review_id': 'VqaiyIX2lqAaF17ERHVgPg', 'text': "The restaurant was beautiful however a bit loud. We were a party of 11. I started with the aged barrel scotch drink. This was tremendous. They delivered an olive tapenade bread with butter after the drinks were delivered. This was good. I had the short rib and mashed potatoes. The short ribs, kale and sauce was amazing however the mashed potatoes was way too syrupy and thin. I think they added this sweet sauce to the mashed potatoes. Someone ordered the mashed potatoes as a side and it was very good not like the side on my plate. The rack of lamb came almost raw and wasn't sent back because she was too shy. The beans under the lamb were hard.  She did try to tell the waiter she didn't like them and he promptly brought the exact same beans to the table. She sent those back and got the mashed potatoes. The grapefruit salad was amazing. The meatloaf was truly amazing. Best ever anywhere! Mac N Cheese was very good not great. The waiter delivered a hard sugar cookie packaged in plastic wrap for the birthday guest. It was what you would expect from Subway yet not as good. The service was very good. There was a waiter in the corner watching our table at all times. All we had to do was look up. Very cool. On the whole the experience was very good not great.", 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 4, 'date': '2015-12-20', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 0, 'useful': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'user_id': '9gK9KtgqJawfctRIoWWErw', 'review_id': '2keNMO6dnF2jaYKzq-84LQ', 'text': 'Absolutely love this place as well as the sister restaurants, Cowboy Ciao and The Gladly. I highly recommend the famous Chop Salad and mac and cheese. They have a great drink selection and romantic environment.  I would highly recommend this place for your next date night or night our with the gang. Also in walking distance to the Old Town bars which make this a great spot to hit before a night out on the town.', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-12-21', 'type': 'review'}
{'votes': {'funny': 1, 'useful': 3, 'cool': 2}, 'user_id': 'mF-Q6qj6GKfk6MU5am6_-Q', 'review_id': 'eLz8OfV9p_8lJ3_qUn2K6Q', 'text': 'So much fun and so good!  Started with happy hour and we drank a whole bunch of the seasonal mule(strawberry, balsamic vinegar mix - i think);  \n\nFor dinner I had the Bavette medium rare which was unbelievably good, along with the risotto and mushrooms sides, I did not ever want to finish.\n\nI so love this place!', 'business_id': 'MuIXnv7Oq7X3-4aEsp9dDA', 'stars': 5, 'date': '2015-12-23', 'type': 'review'}
